WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:49.500 --> 00:00:51.903
<i><b>YOUNG MAN: I didn't really have
your typical upbringing.</b></i>

3
00:00:52.037 --> 00:00:55.674
<i>I mean. I did at first.
but then the world ended.</i>

4
00:00:55.806 --> 00:00:57.475
<i>I don't think anyone
was really shocked.</i>

5
00:00:57.608 --> 00:01:01.011
<i>We always thought it might.
and then it just finally happened.</i>

6
00:01:01.144 --> 00:01:04.817
<i>But how it happened.
now that's where it gets interesting.</i>

7
00:01:05.416 --> 00:01:06.718
<i>Agatha 616.</i>

8
00:01:06.850 --> 00:01:09.319
<i>Yep. an asteroid
heading straight for Earth.</i>

9
00:01:09.454 --> 00:01:11.122
<i>I know. So obvious.</i>

10
00:01:11.255 --> 00:01:13.791
<i>So. humanity came together.
and we did what we do best.</i>

11
00:01:13.925 --> 00:01:15.460
<i>We shot a bunch
of rockets at it!</i>

12
00:01:15.592 --> 00:01:17.728
<i>And we blew it up!
And it was great!</i>

13
00:01:17.862 --> 00:01:20.997
<i>But it wasn't. You see.
the thing that makes rockets rockets...</i>

14
00:01:21.131 --> 00:01:22.701
<i>chemical compounds.
a lot of 'em.</i>

15
00:01:22.833 --> 00:01:26.204
<i>Which rained back down on us.
and everything changed.</i>

16
00:01:26.336 --> 00:01:28.705
<i>And by "everything."
I mean cold-blooded creatures.</i>

17
00:01:28.839 --> 00:01:32.175
<i>And by "changed." I mean mutated
and started eating us to death.</i>

18
00:01:33.678 --> 00:01:37.916
<i>Ants. lizards. roaches. crocodiles.
You name it. There's a lot of 'em.</i>

19
00:01:39.517 --> 00:01:40.819
<b>[WINGS FLAPPING]</b>

20
00:01:40.951 --> 00:01:42.853
<b>- [MAN SCREAMS]
- [LOUD SQUISH]</b>

21
00:01:42.987 --> 00:01:46.590
<i>I knew this one kid who was eaten in his
sleep by a goldfish he won at a carnival.</i>

22
00:01:46.723 --> 00:01:49.127
<i><b>- [GROWLS]
- Man. Todd loved that goldfish.</b></i>

23
00:01:49.261 --> 00:01:50.528
<b>[CAT YOWLS]</b>

24
00:01:50.660 --> 00:01:52.996
<i><b>- And that cat.
- [GOLDFISH BURPS]</b></i>

25
00:01:53.130 --> 00:01:55.900
<i>So. for most of human history.
if you wanted to kill a cockroach.</i>

26
00:01:56.034 --> 00:01:57.436
<i>all you needed was a shoe.</i>

27
00:01:57.568 --> 00:01:59.436
<i>Well. suddenly
you needed a shotgun.</i>

28
00:01:59.571 --> 00:02:01.706
<i>And sometimes even a tank.</i>

29
00:02:01.839 --> 00:02:03.707
<i>And sometimes
even that doesn't work.</i>

30
00:02:03.841 --> 00:02:07.211
<i>Especially if you don't stay
in the tank. Bob.</i>

31
00:02:08.647 --> 00:02:12.149
<i>Eventually. the really big ones and
our military took each other out.</i>

32
00:02:13.417 --> 00:02:18.189
<i>We lost 95% of the human
population in about a year.</i>

33
00:02:18.322 --> 00:02:20.123
<i>That's a lot of Bobs.</i>

34
00:02:20.257 --> 00:02:21.391
<i>And a lot of Todds.</i>

35
00:02:22.493 --> 00:02:25.964
<i>Those of us who survived.
we hid anywhere we could...</i>

36
00:02:26.096 --> 00:02:29.766
<i>bunkers. caves. panic rooms.
all around the world.</i>

37
00:02:29.900 --> 00:02:33.737
<i>So for the last seven years I've
been living in an underground bunker.</i>

38
00:02:34.705 --> 00:02:36.907
<i>It's not as bad
as it sounds. Really.</i>

39
00:02:37.042 --> 00:02:40.412
<i>It's a great group of people.
and we all love each other.</i>

40
00:02:40.544 --> 00:02:43.881
<i>It's kinda what I imagined
college would have been like.</i>

41
00:02:44.016 --> 00:02:47.185
<b>- [PANTING]
- WOMAN: Are you sure he's asleep?</b>

42
00:02:47.317 --> 00:02:48.820
<b>MAN: Who?</b>

43
00:02:48.953 --> 00:02:51.189
- Joel. Who else?
- Yeah. He's asleep.

44
00:02:51.322 --> 00:02:54.025
<b>- WOMAN: Hang on. Shh.
- MAN: He's not awake.</b>

45
00:02:54.159 --> 00:02:55.792
<b>- WOMAN: Are you sure?
- It's just you.</b>

46
00:02:55.927 --> 00:02:57.728
<b>WOMAN: I just... I don't...</b>

47
00:02:57.863 --> 00:03:00.264
<b>MAN: Joel. Joel.</b>

48
00:03:01.031 --> 00:03:03.802
<b>[WHISPERING] See?
He's not awake.</b>

49
00:03:03.935 --> 00:03:05.735
<b>- It's just you.
- [WOMAN SIGHS]</b>

50
00:03:05.870 --> 00:03:08.173
<i><b>JOEL: Dear Aimee. I am wide awake.</b></i>

51
00:03:08.305 --> 00:03:11.576
<i>I've just gotten good at not
really moving or breathing.</i>

52
00:03:11.709 --> 00:03:13.345
<b>[WOMAN MOANING SOFTLY]</b>

53
00:03:13.477 --> 00:03:15.423
<i>Being stuck in a survival
bunker with a bunch of people</i>

54
00:03:15.447 --> 00:03:18.716
<i>who have all found their
soul mate is less than ideal.</i>

55
00:03:18.850 --> 00:03:21.251
<i>Karen and Ray got together
a few months ago.</i>

56
00:03:21.385 --> 00:03:23.421
<i>so they're still kinda
in their honeymoon phase.</i>

57
00:03:23.554 --> 00:03:26.391
<i><b>- [KAREN. RAY CONTINUE MOANING]
- It is super physical.</b></i>

58
00:03:26.524 --> 00:03:30.662
<i>Good for them. They're both very
attractive and apparently quite flexible.</i>

59
00:03:30.794 --> 00:03:33.363
<i>Hey. life's short.
Especially down here.</i>

60
00:03:33.497 --> 00:03:35.333
- Oh. Hey. Ava.
- Hey. Joel.

61
00:03:35.465 --> 00:03:38.636
<b>- MAN: Joel. How's it going?
- It's going good. Tim.</b>

62
00:03:38.769 --> 00:03:41.606
- How are you... How are you doing?
- Yeah. good.

63
00:03:41.739 --> 00:03:43.040
Cool.

64
00:03:44.074 --> 00:03:46.543
<b>- I couldn't sleep.
- AVA: Yeah. we know the feeling.</b>

65
00:03:46.678 --> 00:03:49.180
Yeah. Probably not
for the same reasons.

66
00:03:49.314 --> 00:03:53.084
Y-You guys's. uh. door's open.
Is that... Did you know that?

67
00:03:53.217 --> 00:03:55.153
<b>- AVA: Yeah.
- TIM: Yeah. we know.</b>

68
00:03:55.753 --> 00:03:57.287
Okay.

69
00:03:57.422 --> 00:03:59.132
<i><b>JOEL: After Tim's parents were
eaten by a swarm of termites.</b></i>

70
00:03:59.156 --> 00:04:01.692
<i>- he and Ava became inseparable.
- Okay. Good night.</i>

71
00:04:01.827 --> 00:04:03.627
<i><b>- In every way.
- AVA. TIM: Good night.</b></i>

72
00:04:03.762 --> 00:04:07.666
That's the asteroid
they named 616 Agatha.

73
00:04:07.798 --> 00:04:10.601
And these are all the chemical
bombs they sent up to try and...

74
00:04:10.734 --> 00:04:13.204
<i><b>JOEL: So. pretty much everyone's
coupled up down here.</b></i>

75
00:04:13.338 --> 00:04:16.608
<i>Our first baby was born last winter.
It was super emotional.</i>

76
00:04:16.740 --> 00:04:18.510
<i>Welcome to the apocalypse. kid.</i>

77
00:04:18.642 --> 00:04:21.022
<i>The food sucks. At least you'll
never know what you're missing.</i>

78
00:04:21.046 --> 00:04:24.415
<i>Kala and Connor got together
after Carol died.</i>

79
00:04:24.548 --> 00:04:27.618
<i>Carol was a cow who ate a
box of laundry detergent.</i>

80
00:04:27.752 --> 00:04:31.189
<i><b>- And now we only have one cow.
- [COW MOOING]</b></i>

81
00:04:31.322 --> 00:04:32.557
<i>Her name's Gertie.</i>

82
00:04:32.690 --> 00:04:34.159
<i>Gertie is great.</i>

83
00:04:35.325 --> 00:04:37.060
<i>Gertie's not
our only food source.</i>

84
00:04:37.195 --> 00:04:39.072
<i>We actually have a hunting
party that brings back</i>

85
00:04:39.096 --> 00:04:40.832
<i>whatever they can
from the surface.</i>

86
00:04:40.964 --> 00:04:45.036
<i>It was easier in the beginning. you
know. before we ran out of bullets.</i>

87
00:04:45.168 --> 00:04:47.772
<i>Facing down one of those things
with a janky handmade weapon</i>

88
00:04:47.906 --> 00:04:49.874
<i>is no walk in the park.</i>

89
00:04:50.007 --> 00:04:51.209
<i>Or so they tell me.</i>

90
00:04:51.341 --> 00:04:53.945
<i>I-I don't go
on the hunting parties.</i>

91
00:04:54.077 --> 00:04:56.046
<i>They need me in the kitchen.
I'm kinda the. uh...</i>

92
00:04:56.180 --> 00:04:58.014
<i><b>- [CHOPPING]
- ...the chef of the bunker.</b></i>

93
00:04:58.149 --> 00:04:59.951
<i>Everyone likes my minestrone.</i>

94
00:05:01.351 --> 00:05:04.954
<i>Being the only single person in
the bunker has its perks too.</i>

95
00:05:05.089 --> 00:05:06.558
<i>I get to hang out with Mavis.</i>

96
00:05:06.690 --> 00:05:10.161
<i>Of course. she's not much
for conversation anymore.</i>

97
00:05:10.295 --> 00:05:13.731
<i>Her core battery's shot.
just like every other Mavis. I'd imagine.</i>

98
00:05:13.865 --> 00:05:15.734
<i>Actually never seen
a working one.</i>

99
00:05:16.700 --> 00:05:18.602
<i><b>MAN: ♪ This is the day ♪</b></i>

100
00:05:18.736 --> 00:05:21.772
<i>♪ Your life will surely change ♪</i>

101
00:05:21.906 --> 00:05:23.574
<b>[CHATTERING]</b>

102
00:05:23.707 --> 00:05:25.842
<i>♪ This is the day ♪</i>

103
00:05:25.976 --> 00:05:29.079
<i>♪ When things fall into place ♪</i>

104
00:05:29.212 --> 00:05:31.247
<i><b>JOEL: Sure wish you were here. Aimee.</b></i>

105
00:05:31.382 --> 00:05:33.584
<i>I'd love for you
to meet everyone.</i>

106
00:05:33.718 --> 00:05:35.186
<b>JOEL: Oh. yeah.</b>

107
00:05:35.319 --> 00:05:37.788
<i>Maybe we could do a little
target practice together.</i>

108
00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:39.724
<i>It's kinda my thing.</i>

109
00:05:40.524 --> 00:05:42.094
<i>Well...</i>

110
00:05:44.161 --> 00:05:46.230
<b>- Sorry. Mavis.
- [GERTIE MOOS]</b>

111
00:05:46.363 --> 00:05:49.400
<b>[LOUD THUD]</b>

112
00:05:50.668 --> 00:05:53.905
<b>- [RUMBLING]
- [CREATURES SHRIEKING]</b>

113
00:05:55.872 --> 00:05:57.774
<b>[PEOPLE CHATTERING]</b>

114
00:05:57.909 --> 00:05:59.776
<b>CONNOR: Hustle. hustle. people.
We gotta move.</b>

115
00:05:59.909 --> 00:06:02.481
<b>[GRUNTING]
Guys!</b>

116
00:06:03.848 --> 00:06:06.251
Guys! I got the weapons.

117
00:06:06.884 --> 00:06:08.253
- Stay.
- What?

118
00:06:09.384 --> 00:06:10.464
- Get what you need. and let's go.
- What's happening?

119
00:06:10.488 --> 00:06:11.523
What's going on?

120
00:06:11.656 --> 00:06:13.423
<b>- CONNOR: We're breached.
- Breached?</b>

121
00:06:13.558 --> 00:06:15.125
- Joel.
- What do you mean?

122
00:06:15.259 --> 00:06:16.561
Like.
inside the bunker breached?

123
00:06:16.695 --> 00:06:18.262
That's what "breached"
means. kiddo.

124
00:06:20.664 --> 00:06:22.432
<b>[WHISPERS]
Breached.</b>

125
00:06:23.567 --> 00:06:26.370
Anna Lucia and I will engage.
Anderson and Tim. flank us.

126
00:06:26.504 --> 00:06:29.774
Flank 'em. yeah. okay.
Where do you guys need me? The rear. or...

127
00:06:29.906 --> 00:06:31.226
I thought
we were past this. Joel.

128
00:06:31.276 --> 00:06:32.744
Past what?
You need help. I can help.

129
00:06:32.877 --> 00:06:34.879
- Let me help.
- You gonna make me say it?

130
00:06:35.012 --> 00:06:37.548
- Say what?
- You can't handle it. Joel.

131
00:06:37.682 --> 00:06:39.550
- You're shook.
- Okay. yeah.

132
00:06:39.683 --> 00:06:42.320
<b>- So. you guys don't get scared ever?
- CONNOR: We get scared.</b>

133
00:06:42.452 --> 00:06:45.122
<b>TIM: We all get scared. Joel.
but you get really scared.</b>

134
00:06:45.255 --> 00:06:47.534
- We're not trying to make you feel bad.
- We love you. Joel.

135
00:06:47.558 --> 00:06:48.792
<b>CONNOR: But you're unsafe.</b>

136
00:06:48.926 --> 00:06:51.328
<b>- TIM: You're a liability.
- Even on supply runs.</b>

137
00:06:51.461 --> 00:06:53.331
Okay. why did that speech
feel so rehearsed?

138
00:06:53.464 --> 00:06:55.799
<b>- [CREATURE ROARS]
- [LOUD SLAM ON WALL]</b>

139
00:06:55.933 --> 00:06:57.034
<b>- Connor.
- [DEVICE BEEPS]</b>

140
00:06:57.168 --> 00:07:00.071
Okay. 30 meters out. Let's move.

141
00:07:05.610 --> 00:07:06.776
<b>[CREATURE GROWLING]</b>

142
00:07:06.911 --> 00:07:09.881
- Be careful. Connor-Bear.
- I will. Kala-Bee.

143
00:07:13.750 --> 00:07:15.820
<b>[GROWLING CONTINUES]</b>

144
00:07:17.688 --> 00:07:19.390
<b>CONNOR: Load out.</b>

145
00:07:22.959 --> 00:07:24.962
Go with them.

146
00:07:28.332 --> 00:07:30.202
<b>[DOOR CLOSES]</b>

147
00:07:32.469 --> 00:07:34.637
<b>[MONITOR BEEPING]</b>

148
00:07:34.772 --> 00:07:36.507
<b>KAREN: They're getting close.</b>

149
00:07:42.212 --> 00:07:44.047
<b>- [GASPS]
- AVA: Shit.</b>

150
00:07:44.182 --> 00:07:45.683
<b>[KAREN WHISPERS]
Oh. my God.</b>

151
00:07:45.817 --> 00:07:48.417
<b>- ANDERSON: It's got one of 'em.
- KAREN: What about the others?</b>

152
00:07:48.485 --> 00:07:49.887
They're coming back.

153
00:07:50.021 --> 00:07:51.181
<b>- [DOOR LATCH RATTLES]
- Joel!</b>

154
00:07:51.221 --> 00:07:53.623
They need help. I'm going.

155
00:07:54.125 --> 00:07:55.860
<b>KALA: Joel! Wait!</b>

156
00:07:58.896 --> 00:08:01.600
<b>- [FAINT THUMP]
- [CREATURE CHIRPING]</b>

157
00:08:42.340 --> 00:08:44.242
<b>[LOUD ELECTRICAL SPARK]</b>

158
00:08:49.913 --> 00:08:52.149
<b>- [WHISPERING] Connor?
- [FAINT GROAN]</b>

159
00:08:53.518 --> 00:08:54.552
Connor.

160
00:08:56.654 --> 00:08:59.189
<b>[CREATURE GROWLING]</b>

161
00:08:59.957 --> 00:09:03.794
<b>[SQUISHING. MUNCHING]</b>

162
00:09:04.461 --> 00:09:08.232
<b>[CREATURE CHITTERING. GROWLING]</b>

163
00:09:36.092 --> 00:09:39.029
<b>[CREATURE CHIRPING]</b>

164
00:09:40.530 --> 00:09:42.699
<b>- [ARROW FIRES]
- [CREATURE SHRIEKS]</b>

165
00:09:42.833 --> 00:09:45.803
<b>- [SLASHING]
- [OBJECT THUDS]</b>

166
00:09:45.937 --> 00:09:47.671
<b>[CREATURE'S BODY FALLS]</b>

167
00:09:48.038 --> 00:09:49.541
<b>[GURGLES]</b>

168
00:09:52.176 --> 00:09:55.547
<b>[GASPING. EXHALES]</b>

169
00:09:56.947 --> 00:09:59.183
Did I shoot it. or did you?

170
00:10:00.552 --> 00:10:02.120
What do you think?

171
00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:05.255
You.

172
00:10:08.525 --> 00:10:11.795
<i><b>JOEL: Oh. and I have a pretty
severe freezing problem.</b></i>

173
00:10:11.929 --> 00:10:13.597
<i>But I am working on it.</i>

174
00:10:13.731 --> 00:10:17.735
<b>[POP BALLAD PLAYING]</b>

175
00:10:24.208 --> 00:10:26.678
[POP BALLAD CONTINUES PLAYING ON SPEAKER]

176
00:10:26.811 --> 00:10:29.556
<b>- [WOMAN WHISPERING] How is it looking?
- I think it looks really good.</b>

177
00:10:29.580 --> 00:10:31.148
- Does it look like me?
- Yeah.

178
00:10:31.282 --> 00:10:34.719
Are you sure that
this pose looks natural?

179
00:10:34.851 --> 00:10:36.220
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

180
00:10:36.352 --> 00:10:38.322
I think it's really good.

181
00:10:38.456 --> 00:10:40.224
What are you doing?
Don't move.

182
00:10:40.356 --> 00:10:42.793
- Will you let me see it?
- Don't... Don't move. Aimee.

183
00:10:42.927 --> 00:10:44.287
<b>- I really wanna see it.
- [GROWLS]</b>

184
00:10:44.394 --> 00:10:45.962
<b>[LAUGHS]
Can I see it?</b>

185
00:10:46.096 --> 00:10:48.198
Okay.

186
00:10:48.966 --> 00:10:49.966
Okay.

187
00:10:50.034 --> 00:10:51.769
- Ready?
- Mm-hmm.

188
00:10:57.741 --> 00:10:59.043
What do you think?

189
00:11:00.378 --> 00:11:03.348
- Why do I have a beard?
- snickers:

190
00:11:03.481 --> 00:11:05.350
No. that's shading.
I did the shading.

191
00:11:05.482 --> 00:11:08.118
My head is... is so large.

192
00:11:08.251 --> 00:11:11.622
- You have a big head.
- And my hand is so tiny.

193
00:11:11.755 --> 00:11:13.289
You have tiny hands.

194
00:11:13.990 --> 00:11:15.960
I love it. I frickin' love it.

195
00:11:16.092 --> 00:11:19.462
<b>- That's super sweet. 'cause it's terrible.
- [AIMEE LAUGHS]</b>

196
00:11:19.596 --> 00:11:21.531
- I got you something too.
- What?

197
00:11:21.665 --> 00:11:25.535
I don't know if
these are the right ones.

198
00:11:25.669 --> 00:11:28.938
No way. These are the ones
that I-I-I wanted to get.

199
00:11:29.072 --> 00:11:30.442
- Really?
- Yeah.

200
00:11:32.910 --> 00:11:35.012
Ooh. Hello.

201
00:11:35.145 --> 00:11:36.780
- What's happening right now?
- Uh...

202
00:11:36.913 --> 00:11:39.917
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. I'm dancing with my shoulders.

203
00:11:40.051 --> 00:11:41.619
- Oh. yeah.
- Oh. yeah.

204
00:11:41.753 --> 00:11:44.689
<b>- [JOEL MURMURING]
- [POP BALLAD CONTINUES PLAYING]</b>

205
00:11:57.434 --> 00:11:59.770
This has been the best summer
of my life.

206
00:12:00.737 --> 00:12:02.172
Mine too.

207
00:12:06.744 --> 00:12:07.744
Uh-oh.

208
00:12:07.812 --> 00:12:09.580
What are you doing?

209
00:12:09.713 --> 00:12:13.850
- Do you know what time it is?
- Uh. I think it's. like. 6:30.

210
00:12:13.985 --> 00:12:17.187
Aimee. you're...
you're scaring Crocodile Carl.

211
00:12:17.321 --> 00:12:19.290
Okay. look away. Crocodile Carl.

212
00:12:19.423 --> 00:12:22.125
Oh. Look away.
Hey. I get it.

213
00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:23.760
<b>- [AIMEE GIGGLES]
- I get it.</b>

214
00:12:23.894 --> 00:12:27.965
<b>- [KISSING]
- [POP BALLAD CONTINUES PLAYING]</b>

215
00:12:28.097 --> 00:12:30.834
<b>- [SIRENS WAILING]
- [EXPLOSIONS]</b>

216
00:12:33.504 --> 00:12:35.139
<b>[SIRENS CONTINUE WAILING]</b>

217
00:12:35.271 --> 00:12:36.874
We need to go.

218
00:12:37.841 --> 00:12:39.409
I'm scared.

219
00:12:47.918 --> 00:12:49.486
<b>[CREATURE SHRIEKING]</b>

220
00:12:54.591 --> 00:12:57.995
<i><b>JOEL: Dear Aimee. This week has been
especially shitty.</b></i>

221
00:12:58.129 --> 00:13:01.566
<i>We lost Connor to what
looked like a really big ant.</i>

222
00:13:04.434 --> 00:13:06.303
<i>Helps me to draw them.</i>

223
00:13:06.437 --> 00:13:08.371
<i>I try to capture their essence.</i>

224
00:13:08.505 --> 00:13:10.942
<i>scribble down some notes
on how to kill them.</i>

225
00:13:11.808 --> 00:13:12.909
<b>[SIGHS]</b>

226
00:13:13.043 --> 00:13:14.520
<i>Sometimes I think
it's the only way I know</i>

227
00:13:14.544 --> 00:13:16.346
<i>how to cope with these things.</i>

228
00:13:16.480 --> 00:13:19.750
<b>[FREQUENCY SQUEALS. STATIC CRACKLING]</b>

229
00:13:21.918 --> 00:13:24.587
<b>- [SWITCH CLICKS]
- This is 7045. Come in. 3022.</b>

230
00:13:24.721 --> 00:13:27.591
<b>- I repeat. come in. 3022. Over.
- [SWITCH CLICKS]</b>

231
00:13:27.725 --> 00:13:30.527
<i><b>WOMAN: This is 3022.
What is it now. Ray?</b></i>

232
00:13:30.660 --> 00:13:33.830
Hey. Janice. No. it's actually...
It's. uh. Joel.

233
00:13:34.731 --> 00:13:37.367
<i><b>- [CHUCKLES] Oh. Joel.
- Yeah.</b></i>

234
00:13:37.501 --> 00:13:39.303
<i>All right.
Hold on one second.</i>

235
00:13:39.436 --> 00:13:41.437
<i>Aimee. it's Ray!</i>

236
00:13:41.572 --> 00:13:43.908
It's Joel.
Thanks. Janice.

237
00:13:45.609 --> 00:13:48.279
<i><b>- AIMEE: Joel! Hey!
- Hey. Aimee! Hi!</b></i>

238
00:13:48.413 --> 00:13:50.648
<i>- How are you?
- Hi. Yeah. I. uh... I'm good.</i>

239
00:13:50.780 --> 00:13:53.817
<i>- It's so good to hear your voice.
- I'm so sorry.</i>

240
00:13:53.951 --> 00:13:57.221
<i>I heard on the open frequency
that one of you guys got killed.</i>

241
00:13:57.354 --> 00:13:59.389
Yeah. Breached the bunker.

242
00:13:59.523 --> 00:14:01.825
<i>Wow. Actually got inside?</i>

243
00:14:01.958 --> 00:14:05.895
Yeah. It's the first time it's happened.
It was kinda scary.

244
00:14:06.029 --> 00:14:08.231
<i>Did you have to fight it too?</i>

245
00:14:08.365 --> 00:14:10.702
Yeah. Yeah. a little.

246
00:14:10.835 --> 00:14:12.937
I had to fight it a little bit.

247
00:14:13.069 --> 00:14:15.705
Actually got super ripped since
the last time you saw me. so...

248
00:14:15.840 --> 00:14:18.309
<i><b>Oh. Wow! [GIGGLES]
Super ripped. huh?</b></i>

249
00:14:18.442 --> 00:14:23.013
Yeah. I was kidding. I'm not super ripped.
That was just a bad joke.

250
00:14:23.146 --> 00:14:25.382
<i>Well. I'm glad you're okay.</i>

251
00:14:26.183 --> 00:14:28.351
Thanks. Yeah.

252
00:14:28.485 --> 00:14:32.089
<i>I am still kinda blown away that you were
even able to find my colony on this thing.</i>

253
00:14:32.222 --> 00:14:33.756
I know.
It's pretty crazy.

254
00:14:33.890 --> 00:14:36.660
'Cause I found it on the first one.
What are the odds?

255
00:14:36.793 --> 00:14:38.428
<i><b>- [BOTH CHUCKLE]
- AIMEE: Crazy.</b></i>

256
00:14:38.562 --> 00:14:42.166
Yeah. No. I... I called...
I called. like. 90.

257
00:14:42.298 --> 00:14:43.938
<b>- [AIMEE LAUGHS]
- [UNCOMFORTABLE CHUCKLE]</b>

258
00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:48.239
<i>- Hey. you know what I. uh... know what I wish sometimes?
- What?</i>

259
00:14:48.371 --> 00:14:52.809
That I could. like. s-snap my fingers
and be back in that car with you.

260
00:14:55.178 --> 00:14:56.613
Man. that'd be nice.

261
00:14:56.746 --> 00:14:59.282
<i>Yeah. Too bad it's. uh...</i>

262
00:14:59.415 --> 00:15:02.619
<i>you know. impossible.</i>

263
00:15:02.753 --> 00:15:05.790
<i>Kinda feels like everything
is impossible these days.</i>

264
00:15:05.923 --> 00:15:09.693
<i>Taking care of this whole
colony is exhausting.</i>

265
00:15:11.294 --> 00:15:13.731
I. uh...
I-I write you letters.

266
00:15:15.032 --> 00:15:16.401
<i>Really?</i>

267
00:15:17.735 --> 00:15:20.370
Yeah. Yeah.
I-I write you letters sometimes.

268
00:15:20.504 --> 00:15:22.740
<i>- Aw!
- All the time.</i>

269
00:15:23.373 --> 00:15:25.042
<i>I'd love to read 'em.</i>

270
00:15:25.176 --> 00:15:28.012
<b>- Really? I would love to read them to...
- [STATIC SURGES. STOPS]</b>

271
00:15:28.145 --> 00:15:30.947
<b>- No. Aimee?
- [SWITCHES CLICKING]</b>

272
00:15:33.149 --> 00:15:35.484
<b>- Aimee?
- [STATIC BUZZING]</b>

273
00:15:35.519 --> 00:15:36.953
<b>[STATIC STOPS]</b>

274
00:15:38.355 --> 00:15:39.824
<b>[SIGHS]</b>

275
00:15:45.862 --> 00:15:48.699
<i><b>JOEL: We've lost a lot of people
over the years.</b></i>

276
00:15:50.900 --> 00:15:54.005
<i>You'd think you'd get numb
to it after a certain point.</i>

277
00:15:57.173 --> 00:15:58.608
<i>You don't.</i>

278
00:16:01.345 --> 00:16:04.548
<b>[PEOPLE SHOUTING. CHATTERING]</b>

279
00:16:04.681 --> 00:16:07.184
- I'm sorry.
- Thank God! Where have you been. Joel?

280
00:16:07.317 --> 00:16:10.386
We have to go right now.
Say your goodbyes. get in the car.

281
00:16:10.520 --> 00:16:12.298
- I should go.
- Maybe you should come with us.

282
00:16:12.322 --> 00:16:15.793
<b>- No. my mom is waiting. I'm sorry.
- [CREATURE ROARING]</b>

283
00:16:15.926 --> 00:16:18.095
Get in the car!
Aimee. you need to hurry home now!

284
00:16:18.227 --> 00:16:20.664
- I want you to have this.
- What? This is Crocodile Carl.

285
00:16:20.798 --> 00:16:22.231
It's your good luck charm.

286
00:16:22.365 --> 00:16:24.101
- Be careful.
- You too.

287
00:16:30.774 --> 00:16:33.744
<b>- [PEOPLE CONTINUE CHATTERING. SHOUTING]
- [SIRENS WAILING]</b>

288
00:16:33.878 --> 00:16:34.912
Aimee.

289
00:16:36.913 --> 00:16:38.149
I love you.

290
00:16:39.982 --> 00:16:41.084
I love you too.

291
00:16:42.318 --> 00:16:43.887
I'm gonna come find you.

292
00:16:45.021 --> 00:16:46.490
You better.

293
00:16:55.933 --> 00:16:57.433
<i><b>[AIMEE'S VOICE]
You better.</b></i>

294
00:16:57.567 --> 00:16:59.235
<b>ANNA LUCIA: I wanna know how it got in.</b>

295
00:16:59.369 --> 00:17:02.206
<b>RAY: It appears to have ripped
through one of our perimeter defenses.</b>

296
00:17:02.340 --> 00:17:03.808
<b>AVA: What. it ripped through steel?</b>

297
00:17:03.941 --> 00:17:05.918
<b>TIM: Anderson and I resealed
the breach point and the vent.</b>

298
00:17:05.942 --> 00:17:07.342
Nothing's getting
in that way again.

299
00:17:07.377 --> 00:17:08.588
<b>ANDERSON: But why did it happen?</b>

300
00:17:08.612 --> 00:17:09.846
It was a freak occurrence.

301
00:17:09.981 --> 00:17:11.624
There's no reason to think
it'll happen again.

302
00:17:11.648 --> 00:17:15.084
<b>- RAY: We should try to stay calm.
- [ALL ARGUING]</b>

303
00:17:15.218 --> 00:17:18.022
<b>- How far away is Aimee's colony?
- [ARGUING STOPS]</b>

304
00:17:18.721 --> 00:17:20.857
- What?
- Aimee's colony.

305
00:17:21.592 --> 00:17:24.262
- How far away is it?
- About 85 miles.

306
00:17:24.394 --> 00:17:25.772
How long does that take
to get there?

307
00:17:25.796 --> 00:17:27.698
You're not actually thinking
of going?

308
00:17:27.830 --> 00:17:30.667
Tim. just... humor me.

309
00:17:31.368 --> 00:17:35.038
- How long?
- Seven days. Minimum.

310
00:17:35.173 --> 00:17:39.210
An armed and trained hunting party would
be lucky to last 50 miles on the surface.

311
00:17:39.343 --> 00:17:40.711
But you. Joel...

312
00:17:41.444 --> 00:17:43.913
All right. now I need volunteers

313
00:17:44.048 --> 00:17:46.048
to help reinforce
some of the outer perimeter.

314
00:17:46.183 --> 00:17:49.519
<b>- ANNA LUCIA: Yeah. I'm gonna go.
- [ALL CHATTERING]</b>

315
00:17:49.653 --> 00:17:51.087
<b>- Ava's got this.
- KAREN: Exactly.</b>

316
00:17:51.221 --> 00:17:52.623
I'm gonna go.

317
00:17:55.459 --> 00:17:58.029
It's an impossible journey.
Joel.

318
00:18:00.430 --> 00:18:02.099
No. I'm serious.

319
00:18:04.201 --> 00:18:07.203
I love you guys.
but there's one person in this world

320
00:18:07.337 --> 00:18:09.205
who ever truly made me happy.

321
00:18:09.339 --> 00:18:11.541
and she's only 85 miles away.

322
00:18:11.674 --> 00:18:13.778
And I'm gonna go see her.

323
00:18:15.846 --> 00:18:16.981
Whew.

324
00:18:17.781 --> 00:18:18.982
That felt awesome.

325
00:18:19.115 --> 00:18:21.751
<i><b>JOEL: Dear Aimee. I am done hiding.</b></i>

326
00:18:21.885 --> 00:18:23.953
<i>I'm done waiting
for things to get better.</i>

327
00:18:24.087 --> 00:18:26.789
<i>It's time to take matters
into my own hands.</i>

328
00:18:26.923 --> 00:18:29.760
<i>Time to let someone else
make the minestrone.</i>

329
00:18:30.927 --> 00:18:33.596
<i>I'm taking a radio. even though
it doesn't have power.</i>

330
00:18:33.731 --> 00:18:35.266
<i>But I'm gonna take it anyway.</i>

331
00:18:36.200 --> 00:18:38.168
<b>- Wish me luck. Gertie.
- [GERTIE MOOS]</b>

332
00:18:38.301 --> 00:18:40.336
Mavis. take care of her.

333
00:18:40.471 --> 00:18:42.573
You're not joking. are you?

334
00:18:43.173 --> 00:18:44.942
Nope. Nope. I'm not.

335
00:18:45.608 --> 00:18:46.977
He's not joking.

336
00:18:47.111 --> 00:18:49.847
We're not letting you leave.
Joel. You're needed here.

337
00:18:49.981 --> 00:18:52.849
Tim. no. I'm not. Come on.
I don't do anything.

338
00:18:52.983 --> 00:18:57.288
Joel. that's not true. You fix the radio.
You make the minestrone.

339
00:18:59.056 --> 00:19:00.591
<b>[EXHALES]
Okay.</b>

340
00:19:00.723 --> 00:19:02.683
Doesn't sound as important
when I say it out loud.

341
00:19:02.725 --> 00:19:04.560
I appreciate you trying.
Really. I do.

342
00:19:04.694 --> 00:19:06.996
I just don't feel like
I belong anywhere.

343
00:19:07.131 --> 00:19:10.567
I don't really wanna die all alone
at the end of the world. so...

344
00:19:11.067 --> 00:19:12.737
<b>[EXHALES]</b>

345
00:19:15.672 --> 00:19:21.010
Look. I know you guys all just think
of me as. like. some little. pathetic.

346
00:19:21.511 --> 00:19:23.346
adorable hedgehog.

347
00:19:23.480 --> 00:19:24.981
But I can take care of myself.

348
00:19:25.115 --> 00:19:28.219
I'm actually probably a lot
stronger than you might think.

349
00:19:28.719 --> 00:19:29.987
<b>[EXHALES]</b>

350
00:19:30.119 --> 00:19:33.123
- We made you a map.
- Thanks. Karen.

351
00:19:37.394 --> 00:19:39.462
Just... take care.

352
00:19:39.596 --> 00:19:42.766
- Everything will try to kill you.
- Oh.

353
00:19:42.898 --> 00:19:45.068
Be observant.
Use the advantages that you have.

354
00:19:45.202 --> 00:19:47.604
- You're fast and small. so...
- Right.

355
00:19:47.738 --> 00:19:50.607
- Don't fight. Just run and hide.
- Don't fight.

356
00:19:52.542 --> 00:19:54.110
Thanks. Ray.

357
00:19:55.211 --> 00:19:57.714
You're an asshole
if you get eaten.

358
00:20:05.454 --> 00:20:08.024
- Okay.
- Nice.

359
00:20:09.092 --> 00:20:11.261
I love you guys. Tell Aimee
I'll see her in seven days.

360
00:20:11.394 --> 00:20:13.763
<b>- ANDERSON: We believe in you.
- TIM: Love you. buddy.</b>

361
00:20:17.835 --> 00:20:21.072
<b>[GRUNTS. PANTING]</b>

362
00:20:46.596 --> 00:20:47.865
<b>[SNIFFS]</b>

363
00:20:49.598 --> 00:20:51.301
<b>[INHALES DEEPLY]</b>

364
00:20:54.604 --> 00:20:56.173
<b>[EXHALES]</b>

365
00:21:02.413 --> 00:21:04.548
Where am I?

366
00:21:04.682 --> 00:21:06.849
Well. it's not super useful.

367
00:21:07.416 --> 00:21:08.551
Okay. well. you know what?

368
00:21:08.684 --> 00:21:11.154
We know we gotta head west.
Right?

369
00:21:11.888 --> 00:21:14.657
Well. let's just... do that.

370
00:21:14.790 --> 00:21:17.028
Start with something easy. West.

371
00:21:20.029 --> 00:21:22.266
Nope. it's this way.
West is this way.

372
00:21:28.638 --> 00:21:30.173
Shit.

373
00:21:30.307 --> 00:21:32.977
Split the difference.
Go this way.

374
00:21:33.743 --> 00:21:35.945
Done. First decision made.

375
00:21:55.365 --> 00:21:57.767
<i><b>JOEL: Dear Aimee. I am doing it.</b></i>

376
00:21:57.901 --> 00:21:59.503
<i>I'm really doing it!</i>

377
00:21:59.636 --> 00:22:02.940
<i>Honestly. I thought it'd be way worse.
So far. it's not too bad.</i>

378
00:22:03.073 --> 00:22:06.577
<i>I've seen a lot of signs
of death. but no actual death.</i>

379
00:22:06.710 --> 00:22:08.446
<i>So cross your fingers.</i>

380
00:22:10.212 --> 00:22:11.781
Oh.

381
00:22:11.914 --> 00:22:13.183
Monster eggs.

382
00:22:13.317 --> 00:22:15.484
<i>Trying to stay positive.
Weather's nice.</i>

383
00:22:15.617 --> 00:22:19.222
<i>Getting some fresh air.
What else can I tell ya?</i>

384
00:22:22.827 --> 00:22:24.161
Cool.

385
00:22:25.895 --> 00:22:27.764
<b>- Wham-O...
- [CREATURES CHIRPING]</b>

386
00:22:27.897 --> 00:22:30.966
<b>- [WINGS FLUTTERING]
- No.</b>

387
00:22:31.100 --> 00:22:33.702
<b>- [FOOTSTEPS]
- Run and hide.</b>

388
00:22:33.836 --> 00:22:37.240
Hide in the house.
Hide in the house.

389
00:22:59.329 --> 00:23:02.133
<b>- [CREATURE SHRIEKS]
- [CLATTERING. GLASS BREAKING]</b>

390
00:23:35.766 --> 00:23:38.435
<b>[DEEP. LOW CROAKING]</b>

391
00:23:52.816 --> 00:23:54.852
<b>- [BARKS]
- [JOEL WHIMPERS]</b>

392
00:23:55.352 --> 00:23:58.389
<b>[BARKING]</b>

393
00:24:05.862 --> 00:24:07.764
No.

394
00:24:07.896 --> 00:24:10.067
No. no. no. No!

395
00:24:10.200 --> 00:24:12.970
<b>- [BARKING CONTINUES]
- [GRUNTS] No!</b>

396
00:24:13.503 --> 00:24:16.205
<b>No. no. no!
[SCREAMING]</b>

397
00:24:16.339 --> 00:24:19.342
<b>- [GROWLING]
- Yes! Bite it! Bite it off!</b>

398
00:24:19.475 --> 00:24:22.011
<b>[FROG SHRIEKS]</b>

399
00:24:33.257 --> 00:24:35.793
Wait. Wait. wait.
wait. wait. wait!

400
00:24:35.925 --> 00:24:37.560
Where are you going?

401
00:24:41.798 --> 00:24:45.536
<b>[ROARING. CROAKING]</b>

402
00:24:48.404 --> 00:24:49.939
Whoa!

403
00:24:50.073 --> 00:24:52.009
Whoa. that was so cool.

404
00:24:56.946 --> 00:24:58.181
Nice place.

405
00:24:59.615 --> 00:25:01.285
<b>- Can I sit?
- [WHINES]</b>

406
00:25:05.021 --> 00:25:06.322
Thanks.

407
00:25:11.461 --> 00:25:12.761
You all alone?

408
00:25:12.895 --> 00:25:14.663
<b>- [WHINES]
- Yeah.</b>

409
00:25:14.798 --> 00:25:16.165
Me too.

410
00:25:21.938 --> 00:25:24.241
<b>- Boy?
- [GRUNTS]</b>

411
00:25:24.375 --> 00:25:27.611
Is that your name?
Boy? Your name is Boy.

412
00:25:28.978 --> 00:25:30.314
I'm Joel.

413
00:25:31.181 --> 00:25:32.950
Nice to meet ya.

414
00:25:34.050 --> 00:25:37.587
Thanks. uh...
Thanks for saving my life. Boy.

415
00:25:38.521 --> 00:25:40.256
<b>[WHINES]</b>

416
00:25:44.426 --> 00:25:47.096
<b>- [GROWLS. WHINES]
- Is this a dress?</b>

417
00:25:47.230 --> 00:25:49.999
Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh. Sorry.

418
00:25:50.133 --> 00:25:52.336
Okay. I won't touch it again.

419
00:25:54.636 --> 00:25:57.272
Was that your owner's?

420
00:25:57.406 --> 00:25:59.976
It's okay.
You don't have to talk about it.

421
00:26:01.010 --> 00:26:02.678
Sorry.

422
00:26:03.313 --> 00:26:05.716
Wait. Did you think I was her?

423
00:26:06.650 --> 00:26:07.517
Huh.

424
00:26:07.651 --> 00:26:10.387
I'm gonna lie down too.
Is that o...

425
00:26:11.453 --> 00:26:14.558
No. it's okay.
Just my backpack.

426
00:26:17.394 --> 00:26:19.262
<b>[EXHALES]</b>

427
00:26:21.064 --> 00:26:23.033
<b>[GROANS]</b>

428
00:26:24.567 --> 00:26:26.803
You know.
I had a girl. too. once.

429
00:26:26.936 --> 00:26:29.936
Think you would've really liked her.
Yeah. you guys would totally get along.

430
00:26:30.038 --> 00:26:33.710
She loves dogs. I mean. all animals.
She's a big animal lover.

431
00:26:34.477 --> 00:26:36.747
I haven't seen her
in seven years.

432
00:26:36.879 --> 00:26:40.183
Long time. That's why
I'm trying to go find her.

433
00:26:41.384 --> 00:26:44.755
I haven't told anyone this.
but I'm kinda nervous about it.

434
00:26:46.122 --> 00:26:47.524
<b>[BOY WHINING]</b>

435
00:26:53.796 --> 00:26:55.532
Good night. Boy.

436
00:26:58.734 --> 00:27:02.538
<b>[CREATURE CALLING. FAINT]</b>

437
00:27:03.606 --> 00:27:06.210
<b>[CREATURE HONKING RESPONSE. FAINT]</b>

438
00:27:12.115 --> 00:27:15.786
<b>WEAKNESS: dogs.</b>

439
00:27:18.689 --> 00:27:20.324
That's you.

440
00:27:20.456 --> 00:27:23.992
You wouldn't happen to have a power
source to a ham radio in here. would you?

441
00:27:24.126 --> 00:27:25.729
'Cause I have a...

442
00:27:26.195 --> 00:27:27.430
Never mind.

443
00:27:36.006 --> 00:27:38.341
Huh. Lipstick.

444
00:27:38.474 --> 00:27:39.576
Aimee.

445
00:27:40.376 --> 00:27:42.511
Hey. would you mind
if I kept this?

446
00:27:42.645 --> 00:27:43.680
Thanks.

447
00:27:44.280 --> 00:27:46.982
All right. well... this is it.

448
00:27:47.115 --> 00:27:49.051
Thanks for having me.

449
00:27:49.184 --> 00:27:52.788
I should...
stop talking to a dog.

450
00:27:52.923 --> 00:27:53.990
<b>[WHINES]</b>

451
00:27:54.124 --> 00:27:56.692
Okay. I'll see ya.

452
00:28:07.170 --> 00:28:08.638
<b>[SIGHS]
Okay.</b>

453
00:28:09.305 --> 00:28:11.575
<b>- [BUS DOOR OPENS]
- [BOY WHINES]</b>

454
00:28:12.342 --> 00:28:13.543
<b>- Oh.
- [BARKS]</b>

455
00:28:13.675 --> 00:28:16.012
Oh. hey. hey. hey.
No. no. no. None of that.

456
00:28:16.145 --> 00:28:18.214
Something might hear you.

457
00:28:18.882 --> 00:28:20.750
You wanna come with me?

458
00:28:21.417 --> 00:28:23.519
Okay. You can come.

459
00:28:24.221 --> 00:28:25.689
Let's go. Come on.

460
00:28:26.789 --> 00:28:28.357
Uh... What...

461
00:28:30.026 --> 00:28:34.663
Yeah. we can bring that.
You want me to put it in my bag?

462
00:28:34.797 --> 00:28:36.833
<b>[GROWLING]</b>

463
00:28:36.965 --> 00:28:40.035
Okay. It's okay.
I'm gonna keep it safe. I promise.

464
00:28:40.169 --> 00:28:41.771
<b>[GROWLS. GROANS]</b>

465
00:28:41.904 --> 00:28:44.141
Going in the safe backpack.

466
00:28:44.973 --> 00:28:46.076
See?

467
00:28:46.209 --> 00:28:47.744
Okay. you ready?

468
00:28:48.444 --> 00:28:51.013
<b>- Let's go. Come on.
- [BARKS]</b>

469
00:28:51.147 --> 00:28:53.716
Okay. that's really
gonna have to stop.

470
00:28:57.384 --> 00:28:58.856
Feels good. actually.
having company.

471
00:29:02.326 --> 00:29:03.894
<b>- [GROWLS]
- [INSECT SQUEALS]</b>

472
00:29:04.027 --> 00:29:07.331
<i><b>MAN: ♪ There's a weight
That's pressing down ♪</b></i>

473
00:29:08.865 --> 00:29:12.269
<i>♪ Late at night
You can hear the sound ♪</i>

474
00:29:13.904 --> 00:29:17.539
<i>♪ Even the noise you make
When you sleep ♪</i>

475
00:29:17.673 --> 00:29:19.509
<i><b>JOEL: Dear Aimee. Guess what.</b></i>

476
00:29:19.642 --> 00:29:22.679
<i>I got a dog. and he's the coolest.
His name is Boy.</i>

477
00:29:22.813 --> 00:29:24.533
<i>He saved my life
from a giant frog in a pool</i>

478
00:29:24.646 --> 00:29:26.649
<i>who tried to eat me
with his tongue.</i>

479
00:29:26.782 --> 00:29:29.584
<i>And then we hung out on his bus.
Man. do we make a great team.</i>

480
00:29:29.719 --> 00:29:30.787
<b>[WHINES]</b>

481
00:29:30.920 --> 00:29:32.788
<i>We found out we have
a ton in common too.</i>

482
00:29:32.922 --> 00:29:34.990
<i>I feel like
we can talk about anything.</i>

483
00:29:36.158 --> 00:29:39.094
<i>You gotta see us out here.
We're like this iconic duo.</i>

484
00:29:39.228 --> 00:29:42.865
<i>I don't know. Feels like when
we're together. we're unstoppable.</i>

485
00:29:43.000 --> 00:29:45.969
Hey. What are you doing?
What you got in there?

486
00:29:46.102 --> 00:29:47.371
<b>- [CLATTERING]
- [BOY YIPS]</b>

487
00:29:47.503 --> 00:29:49.313
<b>- Oh. my gosh. Yeah. Go. Go!
- [CREATURE CHITTERING]</b>

488
00:29:49.337 --> 00:29:51.340
We gotta go! Come on!

489
00:29:51.473 --> 00:29:54.711
<b>[SONG CONTINUES PLAYING. FAINT]</b>

490
00:29:58.247 --> 00:30:01.218
<b>Berries.
[GASPS]</b>

491
00:30:01.350 --> 00:30:04.154
Sustenance. Perfect.

492
00:30:04.287 --> 00:30:05.654
<b>- [THUMP]
- Ow. Ow!</b>

493
00:30:05.788 --> 00:30:09.326
<b>- [GROWLS]
- Ow! What... What are you doing?</b>

494
00:30:10.225 --> 00:30:12.061
<b>- Uh...
- [BOY BARKING]</b>

495
00:30:12.194 --> 00:30:13.462
<b>[GROWLING]</b>

496
00:30:13.596 --> 00:30:15.432
But they look so good.

497
00:30:15.565 --> 00:30:17.768
<b>[BOY BARKS. WHINES]</b>

498
00:30:19.068 --> 00:30:21.605
Yeah. you know what?
I don't think I should eat these.

499
00:30:21.738 --> 00:30:25.141
<i><b>JOEL: It's crazy the things you forget
about the world. Like the smells.</b></i>

500
00:30:25.275 --> 00:30:27.310
<i>The grass.
the trees. the flowers.</i>

501
00:30:27.442 --> 00:30:29.546
<i>Sure. you get the occasional
bloody corpse. but...</i>

502
00:30:29.680 --> 00:30:30.714
Aaah!

503
00:30:31.413 --> 00:30:34.785
<b>[GROANS. COUGHING]</b>

504
00:30:34.917 --> 00:30:36.886
<b>[LOUD GROAN. SPITS]</b>

505
00:30:39.154 --> 00:30:41.924
<b>[BARKING]</b>

506
00:30:42.058 --> 00:30:44.528
<b>[GRUNTS. SIGHS]</b>

507
00:30:45.294 --> 00:30:48.565
<b>[EXHALING]</b>

508
00:30:51.233 --> 00:30:53.502
<b>[WHISPERS] Oh. no.
I fell in a hole.</b>

509
00:30:53.636 --> 00:30:55.739
<b>- [WHINES]
- Okay. I just gotta...</b>

510
00:30:57.039 --> 00:30:58.340
climb out.

511
00:30:58.473 --> 00:31:00.309
I can climb out.

512
00:31:01.411 --> 00:31:02.980
<b>[CREATURE CHITTERS]</b>

513
00:31:05.182 --> 00:31:06.783
<b>[SNAP]</b>

514
00:31:10.384 --> 00:31:11.384
<b>[WHISPERS]
Oh. no.</b>

515
00:31:12.355 --> 00:31:13.757
This is bad.

516
00:31:14.825 --> 00:31:17.160
<b>- Oh. this is so bad.
- [BARKING]</b>

517
00:31:17.294 --> 00:31:19.396
<b>[WHISPERING]
Stop. Stop it. Shh. Stop it.</b>

518
00:31:19.529 --> 00:31:21.365
<b>[CREATURE CHITTERS]</b>

519
00:31:23.266 --> 00:31:24.901
<b>- [RUSTLING]
- [CHITTERING CONTINUES]</b>

520
00:31:34.510 --> 00:31:36.747
<b>[CHITTERING CONTINUES]</b>

521
00:31:39.949 --> 00:31:43.387
<b>[ROARS. CHITTERING]</b>

522
00:31:52.328 --> 00:31:54.830
<b>- [RUSTLING CONTINUES]
- [CHITTERING CONTINUES]</b>

523
00:32:07.210 --> 00:32:09.178
<b>[GASPS]</b>

524
00:32:09.311 --> 00:32:11.313
It's a rope. you numbskull!

525
00:32:11.448 --> 00:32:13.984
Put it around your foot
and grab on!

526
00:32:14.116 --> 00:32:16.519
<b>Okay. come on! Hold on!
[GRUNTS]</b>

527
00:32:16.653 --> 00:32:19.055
<b>Pull up!
[SCREAMS]</b>

528
00:32:19.188 --> 00:32:20.923
<b>[GRUNTING]</b>

529
00:32:21.057 --> 00:32:22.992
<b>[WHIMPERING]</b>

530
00:32:26.061 --> 00:32:27.229
<b>[GRUNTING]</b>

531
00:32:27.364 --> 00:32:30.667
<b>- You wanna look at 'em? Oh. shit!
- [GROANING]</b>

532
00:32:32.501 --> 00:32:34.805
<b>- [CHITTERING]
- Uh...</b>

533
00:32:35.471 --> 00:32:37.106
Minnow. finish 'em off.

534
00:32:37.240 --> 00:32:38.374
<b>[PIN CLICKS]</b>

535
00:32:38.508 --> 00:32:41.744
One. two. three. four and...

536
00:32:41.877 --> 00:32:42.945
<b>[JOEL YELPS]</b>

537
00:32:45.147 --> 00:32:47.416
<b>Are we...
[GROANS. SPITS]</b>

538
00:32:48.817 --> 00:32:50.654
<b>- [EXHALES]
- Always count to five.</b>

539
00:32:50.787 --> 00:32:52.555
Was that a samurai sword?

540
00:32:52.689 --> 00:32:54.557
Why'd you fall
into a Sandgobbler's nest?

541
00:32:54.690 --> 00:32:57.626
I didn't mean to. you know.
I was just... I was walking.

542
00:32:57.760 --> 00:32:59.995
- What's your name?
- Joel.

543
00:33:00.129 --> 00:33:01.397
Joel Dawson.

544
00:33:01.530 --> 00:33:03.165
I'm. uh. Clyde.
This is Minnow.

545
00:33:03.298 --> 00:33:06.168
You're lucky we weren't monsters.
You were yelling like a girl.

546
00:33:06.301 --> 00:33:08.370
<b>[HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
"This is bad! This is so bad!"</b>

547
00:33:08.504 --> 00:33:12.441
Okay. I don't sound like that.
My voice is not that high-pitched.

548
00:33:12.576 --> 00:33:14.443
- Yeah. it is.
- Yes. it is.

549
00:33:14.577 --> 00:33:16.746
It was higher than mine.
and I'm eight.

550
00:33:16.878 --> 00:33:20.416
What in God's name are you
doing up here alone anyway?

551
00:33:20.549 --> 00:33:22.651
<b>- I'm not alone. I've got Boy too.
- [WHINES]</b>

552
00:33:22.785 --> 00:33:24.687
Oh. wait. no! No. wait. wait!

553
00:33:24.820 --> 00:33:27.557
<b>- [JOEL GROANS]
- Oh. my God. it's a puppy!</b>

554
00:33:27.691 --> 00:33:29.726
<b>MINNOW: Come here. Boy!
Come here. Boy!</b>

555
00:33:29.858 --> 00:33:32.761
- They almost killed my dog.
- Hi. Boy!

556
00:33:32.895 --> 00:33:34.798
<b>- Hi! [GIGGLES]
- [CLYDE CHUCKLES]</b>

557
00:33:34.931 --> 00:33:36.466
Hey.

558
00:33:36.598 --> 00:33:39.467
So. uh. what happened
with your colony. man?

559
00:33:39.602 --> 00:33:41.070
They kick you out?

560
00:33:41.203 --> 00:33:43.205
No. I actually left on my own.

561
00:33:43.338 --> 00:33:46.075
- Something I had to do.
- You stole food. didn't you?

562
00:33:46.209 --> 00:33:47.677
- He's a food stealer.
- Yeah.

563
00:33:47.809 --> 00:33:51.246
- No. I didn't steal any food.
- Right.

564
00:33:51.379 --> 00:33:53.949
Me and my colony were really close.
Like family. Okay?

565
00:33:54.083 --> 00:33:56.086
They were super upset
that I left.

566
00:33:56.219 --> 00:33:59.689
<b>[CREATURE ROARING. FAINT]</b>

567
00:34:00.490 --> 00:34:02.525
- Time to go. Minnow.
- Time to go? Why?

568
00:34:02.658 --> 00:34:04.760
<b>- So. what...
- [GROWLING CONTINUES]</b>

569
00:34:04.894 --> 00:34:07.029
What. uh... What was that?
What's going on?

570
00:34:07.163 --> 00:34:10.533
<b>- Could've been a lot of things.
- MINNOW: Tree Flamer. Herd Stomper.</b>

571
00:34:10.665 --> 00:34:12.100
<b>[SCOFFS]
Rockdiver.</b>

572
00:34:12.234 --> 00:34:16.138
Limbsnapper. Limbcrusher.
And my favorite... the Chumbler.

573
00:34:16.272 --> 00:34:19.475
<b>JOEL: Okay. I get it.
A lot of... A lot of names.</b>

574
00:34:19.609 --> 00:34:23.212
<b>CLYDE: Whatever it is.
it took your screams for the dinner bell.</b>

575
00:34:23.345 --> 00:34:26.481
If it's got your scent.
it's gonna be on you for a while.

576
00:34:26.616 --> 00:34:30.220
Hey. maybe I could. like.
I don't know. come with you guys.

577
00:34:35.057 --> 00:34:36.926
<b>CLYDE: Which way you headed?</b>

578
00:34:37.627 --> 00:34:39.295
Going west.

579
00:34:39.428 --> 00:34:41.863
To the coast. Jenner Beach.

580
00:34:41.997 --> 00:34:44.265
Yeah. We're not
cutting north just yet.

581
00:34:44.399 --> 00:34:47.702
- Not cu... Not cutting north just yet.
- Come on. Come on.

582
00:34:47.837 --> 00:34:49.872
Yeah. Whatever you want.

583
00:34:50.006 --> 00:34:52.107
You guys want me
to come. I'll come.

584
00:34:52.241 --> 00:34:54.109
Come on.

585
00:35:13.763 --> 00:35:16.732
That's a good. uh...
good little workout.

586
00:35:18.433 --> 00:35:20.470
<b>CLYDE: A girl. huh?</b>

587
00:35:20.602 --> 00:35:22.171
<b>Yeah.
[GROANS]</b>

588
00:35:22.305 --> 00:35:24.785
You left a nice. safe colony to
travel all the way to the ocean

589
00:35:24.874 --> 00:35:28.278
for a girl you ain't seen
since you were. what. 17?

590
00:35:28.410 --> 00:35:31.747
No. I know what you're thinking.
I know how it sounds. It's crazy.

591
00:35:31.881 --> 00:35:33.415
But... I don't know.

592
00:35:33.549 --> 00:35:36.419
If you knew our connection.
you'd probably feel differently.

593
00:35:36.551 --> 00:35:39.388
We actually just got back in touch
over the radio a few weeks ago.

594
00:35:39.522 --> 00:35:42.625
And it's still there.
It's just magical. And so sweet.

595
00:35:42.758 --> 00:35:45.994
She loves me too. so a "pick up right
where we left off" kind of thing.

596
00:35:46.127 --> 00:35:49.298
- It's still there.
- You ever hear the term "fool's errand"?

597
00:35:49.432 --> 00:35:52.769
All right. what. so I'm a fool
because I believe in true love?

598
00:35:52.901 --> 00:35:55.170
No. you're a fool
because you're out here alone.

599
00:35:55.305 --> 00:35:57.741
you don't know a thing
about survival...

600
00:35:59.241 --> 00:36:00.241
Wind.

601
00:36:00.308 --> 00:36:02.011
...you shoot for shit.

602
00:36:02.144 --> 00:36:06.615
yet you got an attitude like
you're some kind of noble warrior

603
00:36:06.749 --> 00:36:08.984
floating on the wings of love.

604
00:36:09.118 --> 00:36:12.387
- Doesn't work like that.
- Okay.

605
00:36:12.520 --> 00:36:14.990
Super encouraging speech.

606
00:36:22.397 --> 00:36:23.732
- Damn it.
- You're braining out.

607
00:36:23.866 --> 00:36:26.803
- Huh?
- Braining out. Thinking too much.

608
00:36:26.937 --> 00:36:30.240
I always clear my mind
and say to myself.

609
00:36:30.372 --> 00:36:31.508
"a needle through water."

610
00:36:31.640 --> 00:36:33.142
"A needle through water"?

611
00:36:33.276 --> 00:36:36.379
Trust me. My dad was the
best archer in my colony.

612
00:36:36.513 --> 00:36:40.749
Oh. really? Okay. Then how come he's
not the one giving me the lessons?

613
00:36:40.883 --> 00:36:42.384
'Cause I'm not her dad.

614
00:36:42.517 --> 00:36:44.486
Yeah. my dad got killed.

615
00:36:44.620 --> 00:36:46.756
Back when we lived
in the subway station.

616
00:36:46.890 --> 00:36:48.424
Along with Elliot.

617
00:36:48.557 --> 00:36:50.325
Uh. wh-who's Elliot?

618
00:36:50.459 --> 00:36:51.794
My son.

619
00:36:52.761 --> 00:36:55.732
- Oh. I'm sorry.
- No need to be sorry.

620
00:36:56.866 --> 00:36:59.202
We all have stories like that.
Don't we?

621
00:37:05.841 --> 00:37:07.243
Needle through water.

622
00:37:08.743 --> 00:37:10.779
<b>[MUTTERS]
Needle through water.</b>

623
00:37:14.616 --> 00:37:16.618
Hey. that was pretty close.

624
00:37:16.752 --> 00:37:19.088
- It was better.
- It was really good. right?

625
00:37:20.055 --> 00:37:21.523
Right?

626
00:37:21.656 --> 00:37:25.428
Tell you what. kid. You gonna hang with
us. you need to know stuff.

627
00:37:25.562 --> 00:37:26.663
Yeah. Okay.

628
00:37:26.796 --> 00:37:28.830
- First lesson.
- Yeah. Hit me.

629
00:37:28.964 --> 00:37:31.366
Always survey from high ground
when possible.

630
00:37:31.499 --> 00:37:32.635
- Always.
- Always.

631
00:37:32.769 --> 00:37:34.289
Helps you spot the big ones
in advance.

632
00:37:34.336 --> 00:37:36.313
It's nice to know that thing's
not following us anymore.

633
00:37:36.337 --> 00:37:39.642
No. no. it's definitely still
following us. Just saw it.

634
00:37:39.774 --> 00:37:41.309
- What...
- Yeah.

635
00:37:41.444 --> 00:37:43.880
- Chumbler.
- I knew it.

636
00:37:44.013 --> 00:37:46.982
- Big son of a bitch too.
- Big sumanabitch.

637
00:37:47.116 --> 00:37:49.018
<b>- [GROANS]
- Got your scent too. man.</b>

638
00:37:49.151 --> 00:37:52.421
- It's gonna be hard to shake.
- Then why are we still standing here?

639
00:37:52.555 --> 00:37:54.890
Relax.
Chumblers aren't fast.

640
00:37:55.024 --> 00:37:56.792
- We gotta keep moving.
- Mmm.

641
00:37:56.926 --> 00:37:58.895
Should've already been gone.

642
00:38:00.196 --> 00:38:03.299
<b>- It's got my scent.
- CLYDE: Oh. yeah. it does.</b>

643
00:38:05.700 --> 00:38:09.338
<b>[GROWLING]</b>

644
00:38:12.774 --> 00:38:14.677
<b>- CLYDE: Comin'?
- Yeah!</b>

645
00:38:16.444 --> 00:38:18.548
<b>- Where you guys headed anyway?
- CLYDE: North.</b>

646
00:38:18.680 --> 00:38:20.849
- To the mountains.
- What's up there?

647
00:38:20.984 --> 00:38:23.419
A. uh. place called
Snow Mountain Wilderness.

648
00:38:23.553 --> 00:38:26.823
Supposed to be some kind of
colony up there full of survivors.

649
00:38:26.955 --> 00:38:29.724
The cold and elevation
help to keep the monsters away.

650
00:38:29.859 --> 00:38:31.994
You should definitely
come with us.

651
00:38:32.127 --> 00:38:33.763
Well. I would. but. you know...

652
00:38:33.895 --> 00:38:35.830
You gotta go
find your girlfriend.

653
00:38:35.964 --> 00:38:37.467
- Yeah. yeah.
- Uh...

654
00:38:40.535 --> 00:38:41.970
Minnow.

655
00:38:42.937 --> 00:38:44.606
If you knew her.
you'd really like her.

656
00:38:44.740 --> 00:38:45.875
She's a super cool person.

657
00:38:46.008 --> 00:38:47.442
Well. she's not gonna like you.

658
00:38:47.575 --> 00:38:50.412
'cause you can't even get out
of a Sandgobbler's nest.

659
00:38:50.546 --> 00:38:53.815
And honestly. I just like you
'cause you have a really cute dog.

660
00:38:53.950 --> 00:38:57.453
- Hurts my feelings.
- You're so useless.

661
00:38:57.587 --> 00:38:59.055
<b>[CLYDE GRUNTS]</b>

662
00:38:59.187 --> 00:39:01.758
It just means
she likes you. man.

663
00:39:01.890 --> 00:39:04.359
She's. uh...
She's been through a lot.

664
00:39:06.361 --> 00:39:07.361
Yeah.

665
00:39:07.462 --> 00:39:09.499
So annoying.

666
00:39:10.633 --> 00:39:12.769
- Joel.
- What?

667
00:39:13.403 --> 00:39:14.970
Don't move.

668
00:39:15.104 --> 00:39:17.240
- Oh. my God. Why?
- Give me your shirt.

669
00:39:17.372 --> 00:39:19.307
<b>- [RUMBLING]
- My shirt? What do you mean?</b>

670
00:39:19.441 --> 00:39:22.144
Your shirt. man.
Give me your shirt.

671
00:39:22.278 --> 00:39:24.680
- Okay.
- Get... Hurr... Come on.

672
00:39:24.814 --> 00:39:27.616
- Do what he says. Joel.
- Give me your shirt.

673
00:39:27.750 --> 00:39:29.510
<b>- [RUMBLING CONTINUES]
- Shut up. I'm trying.</b>

674
00:39:29.618 --> 00:39:31.287
Easy. Take it easy.

675
00:39:32.221 --> 00:39:34.156
- That's it. That's it.
- Is it a Chumbler?

676
00:39:34.290 --> 00:39:36.358
<b>- No.
- [WHIMPERS] What is it called?</b>

677
00:39:36.959 --> 00:39:39.562
Take it easy. Lean over. man.

678
00:39:39.696 --> 00:39:41.130
- If I don't make it...
- Shh. shh.

679
00:39:41.263 --> 00:39:43.933
<b>- That's it. That's it.
- [GASPING. WHIMPERING]</b>

680
00:39:46.067 --> 00:39:47.502
<b>- [GASPS]
- Shh. shh. shh. shh.</b>

681
00:39:47.636 --> 00:39:50.306
Just stay very still.

682
00:39:50.439 --> 00:39:53.843
<b>- [TREMBLING WHISPER] Okay.
- Shh.</b>

683
00:39:54.676 --> 00:39:56.144
<b>CLYDE: Okay. buddy.</b>

684
00:39:56.278 --> 00:39:58.680
<b>[GROWLS]</b>

685
00:39:58.814 --> 00:40:01.984
Shh. shh. shh. shh.
Easy does it.

686
00:40:02.118 --> 00:40:05.020
<b>- [GROWLING CONTINUES]
- It's okay.</b>

687
00:40:06.256 --> 00:40:07.690
You're okay.

688
00:40:07.823 --> 00:40:11.194
It's okay.
You're all right.

689
00:40:11.993 --> 00:40:14.363
All right. Okay. now.

690
00:40:15.096 --> 00:40:18.234
<b>- On your way.
- [ROARS]</b>

691
00:40:18.667 --> 00:40:19.935
Okay. now.

692
00:40:22.071 --> 00:40:24.773
<b>- All good. On your way now.
- [ROARING CONTINUES]</b>

693
00:40:24.906 --> 00:40:26.241
On your way.

694
00:40:28.176 --> 00:40:30.512
Good boy. Good boy.

695
00:40:38.087 --> 00:40:40.690
What you so scared for?
Boulder Snails are nice.

696
00:40:41.223 --> 00:40:42.725
There can be nice ones?

697
00:40:42.859 --> 00:40:46.161
You can always tell in their eyes.
Just look at their eyes.

698
00:40:46.294 --> 00:40:49.231
<b>- This one probably saved our lives too.
- [WHISPERS] Saved our...</b>

699
00:40:49.365 --> 00:40:52.401
Gonna spread your scent
all over this hillside.

700
00:40:52.535 --> 00:40:56.272
Shoot. That old Chumbler ain't
gonna know which way to go.

701
00:40:56.406 --> 00:40:58.607
<b>JOEL: So the Chumbler's gonna follow my shirt?</b>

702
00:40:58.741 --> 00:41:01.176
<b>- [BOULDER SNAIL ROARS]
- Thank you. Mr. Boulder Snail.</b>

703
00:41:01.310 --> 00:41:04.314
<b>- Thank you. Mr. Boulder Snail!
- [SLURRED] Thank you.</b>

704
00:41:04.446 --> 00:41:06.948
<b>CLYDE: Yeah. they're very sensitive. you know.</b>

705
00:41:07.082 --> 00:41:08.082
<b>[JOEL WHIMPERS]</b>

706
00:41:08.149 --> 00:41:10.619
But they'll crush your ass...

707
00:41:11.620 --> 00:41:13.356
in a second.

708
00:41:14.455 --> 00:41:18.627
<b>[CREATURES ROARING. CHITTERING. FAINT]</b>

709
00:41:19.528 --> 00:41:21.163
<b>CLYDE: What you working on. man?</b>

710
00:41:21.296 --> 00:41:25.566
Just a little project I started
a while back in my colony.

711
00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:30.338
Every time we encountered a new
monster. I'd just make a little entry.

712
00:41:30.471 --> 00:41:31.707
<b>CLYDE: Mm-hmm.</b>

713
00:41:31.841 --> 00:41:34.611
A drawing.
Um. just some info about it.

714
00:41:34.743 --> 00:41:37.178
You know. strengths. weaknesses.
Stuff like that.

715
00:41:37.312 --> 00:41:39.781
Made me feel like
I was helping out. you know.

716
00:41:39.915 --> 00:41:42.950
- You're a pretty good artist.
- Thanks.

717
00:41:43.084 --> 00:41:45.820
- I seen this one. Ugly bastard.
- Yeah.

718
00:41:45.955 --> 00:41:47.523
- Doesn't like loud noises.
- Oh. yeah.

719
00:41:47.656 --> 00:41:50.760
Also doesn't like
shotgun blasts to the head.

720
00:41:50.892 --> 00:41:52.593
Might wanna add that.

721
00:41:53.127 --> 00:41:55.163
Shotgun to the face.

722
00:41:55.296 --> 00:41:56.664
- Yeah. Got it.
- Oh.

723
00:41:56.799 --> 00:41:58.734
- Do you mind if I...
- Oh. sure.

724
00:41:58.866 --> 00:42:01.035
Yeah. Oh. thanks. Thanks.

725
00:42:01.537 --> 00:42:03.772
- Oh. wow.
- Yeah.

726
00:42:03.906 --> 00:42:05.808
I was 16 when it hit.

727
00:42:05.941 --> 00:42:08.410
Yeah. they sent everything
up at once to take her down.

728
00:42:08.544 --> 00:42:11.080
They had the balls
to call us the lucky ones

729
00:42:11.212 --> 00:42:14.549
just 'cause whatever the hell was
in those things didn't affect us.

730
00:42:14.683 --> 00:42:18.955
Ain't nothing lucky about getting
kicked off the top of the food chain.

731
00:42:19.087 --> 00:42:23.426
Yeah. my parents thought if we
could just make it out of Fairfield.

732
00:42:23.558 --> 00:42:24.892
we might have a shot.

733
00:42:25.026 --> 00:42:26.595
Wait. wait. wait.

734
00:42:27.995 --> 00:42:29.865
You're from Fairfield?

735
00:42:29.997 --> 00:42:32.100
Yeah. Why?

736
00:42:33.535 --> 00:42:36.904
Man. I've never met anyone
who made it out of Fairfield.

737
00:42:37.038 --> 00:42:39.975
That place
was basically ground zero.

738
00:42:40.109 --> 00:42:43.546
Shit. I've only heard
horror stories.

739
00:42:45.113 --> 00:42:46.749
Yeah. it was pretty bad.

740
00:42:46.881 --> 00:42:48.584
Your parents. uh...

741
00:42:49.051 --> 00:42:50.486
Oh. uh. no.

742
00:42:50.618 --> 00:42:53.689
<b>[CLEARS THROAT]
No. it's just me.</b>

743
00:42:56.526 --> 00:42:58.227
Couldn't save 'em.

744
00:42:58.928 --> 00:43:00.997
You putting that on yourself?

745
00:43:01.462 --> 00:43:03.298
Mmm.

746
00:43:04.332 --> 00:43:06.135
<b>[SIGHS]
You're from Fairfield. man.</b>

747
00:43:06.267 --> 00:43:08.470
You shouldn't even be here.
Right?

748
00:43:08.604 --> 00:43:11.607
You're more of a survivor
than I thought.

749
00:43:14.575 --> 00:43:17.479
That's the coolest thing
anyone's ever said to me.

750
00:43:18.180 --> 00:43:19.982
It's a good start.

751
00:43:20.115 --> 00:43:24.520
Keep it up. Book like this could
save someone's life out here.

752
00:43:25.921 --> 00:43:26.955
Thanks. Clyde.

753
00:43:27.089 --> 00:43:28.658
<b>[BOY WHINES]</b>

754
00:43:28.790 --> 00:43:30.125
You. um...

755
00:43:31.160 --> 00:43:33.029
sure your girl's worth it?

756
00:43:33.696 --> 00:43:35.298
Coming all this way?

757
00:43:37.933 --> 00:43:39.301
Yeah.

758
00:43:39.801 --> 00:43:41.037
Yeah. she is.

759
00:43:42.205 --> 00:43:43.673
<b>MINNOW: Don't settle. Joel.</b>

760
00:43:45.575 --> 00:43:47.176
She's right.

761
00:43:47.310 --> 00:43:49.212
You don't have to.

762
00:43:50.178 --> 00:43:52.582
Not even at
the end of the world.

763
00:43:54.182 --> 00:43:56.051
<b>[JOEL GROANS]</b>

764
00:44:04.894 --> 00:44:07.662
<b>- [BOY WHINES]
- Okay! Time to break camp! Let's go!</b>

765
00:44:07.796 --> 00:44:09.598
<b>JOEL: Uh. wh...</b>

766
00:44:09.732 --> 00:44:11.099
Lesson two.

767
00:44:11.232 --> 00:44:14.169
You get a hot meal
or a good night's sleep.

768
00:44:14.303 --> 00:44:16.672
- Not both.
- Not both.

769
00:44:16.805 --> 00:44:18.640
Are you being serious?

770
00:44:18.774 --> 00:44:21.051
Something will have smelled our food and
be all over this camp within the hour.

771
00:44:21.075 --> 00:44:25.079
Why wouldn't you tell me that. though?
Uh. I didn't... I didn't do either.

772
00:44:25.214 --> 00:44:28.116
I can't tell you everything.
man. Keep up.

773
00:44:35.991 --> 00:44:38.561
<b>[CHITTERING. FAINT]</b>

774
00:44:38.694 --> 00:44:42.998
"Roar! I'm gonna kill you. Joel Dawson!
I'm gonna eat you like broccoli!"

775
00:44:43.131 --> 00:44:45.133
<b>[MINNOW GROWLING]</b>

776
00:44:45.267 --> 00:44:46.987
"I'm Joel.
and I can't protect my girlfriend

777
00:44:47.102 --> 00:44:50.404
because I'm useless and insecure
and an awkward little teenager."

778
00:44:50.538 --> 00:44:52.674
"But I need you to save me!
I thought you loved me."

779
00:44:52.807 --> 00:44:56.344
<b>"But I can't because..."
[SPUTTERING. SHRIEKING]</b>

780
00:44:56.477 --> 00:44:58.513
- What?
- That's your girlfriend dying.

781
00:44:58.647 --> 00:45:00.883
- What?
- A needle through water.

782
00:45:01.750 --> 00:45:04.653
A needle through water.
Needle through water.

783
00:45:06.421 --> 00:45:10.092
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!
Yes! See? Bull's-eye!

784
00:45:10.625 --> 00:45:12.361
<b>[GROANS]
Oh.</b>

785
00:45:12.493 --> 00:45:14.261
Got yourself
an admirer there. huh?

786
00:45:14.395 --> 00:45:16.499
Hey. we gotta get going.

787
00:45:16.631 --> 00:45:18.165
Uh. okay.

788
00:45:18.299 --> 00:45:20.535
Come on. Come on.
We gotta go. We...

789
00:45:21.504 --> 00:45:23.873
Minnow? What are you doing?

790
00:45:24.707 --> 00:45:27.576
<i><b>JOEL: Dear Aimee. I made friends.</b></i>

791
00:45:27.709 --> 00:45:28.877
<i>Human friends.</i>

792
00:45:29.011 --> 00:45:30.771
<i>And they're teaching me
everything they know.</i>

793
00:45:30.879 --> 00:45:32.147
<b>[CREATURE SQUEALS]</b>

794
00:45:32.281 --> 00:45:35.317
<i>Like lesson three:
Don't take shortcuts.</i>

795
00:45:37.785 --> 00:45:40.923
<i>Lesson eight:
Target practice every day.</i>

796
00:45:41.055 --> 00:45:42.655
<i>I'm getting pretty good
with my crossbow.</i>

797
00:45:42.758 --> 00:45:44.625
<b>- [MINNOW LAUGHS] See?
- CLYDE: Pretty good.</b>

798
00:45:44.760 --> 00:45:48.631
<i>Lesson ten: Keep your socks dry.
That's a great one.</i>

799
00:45:49.732 --> 00:45:52.435
<i>I'm kinda struggling
with lesson two: Not both.</i>

800
00:45:52.567 --> 00:45:54.270
<i>That one is not great.</i>

801
00:45:55.104 --> 00:45:57.205
<b>CLYDE: Not both. Not both.</b>

802
00:45:57.339 --> 00:45:59.808
<b>[CLAP]
- Come on. Joel. Not both.</b>

803
00:45:59.941 --> 00:46:01.776
<i>I'm super tired.</i>

804
00:46:10.118 --> 00:46:13.556
All right. a lot of things out
here you shouldn't touch or eat.

805
00:46:13.689 --> 00:46:17.225
but. uh. ferns like these
have an antivenom.

806
00:46:17.359 --> 00:46:20.563
Good in a pinch
for snakes. slugs.

807
00:46:20.696 --> 00:46:23.132
- Great entry for your book.
- Yep. got it.

808
00:46:24.066 --> 00:46:27.169
The insect-looking ones
got no peripheral vision.

809
00:46:27.301 --> 00:46:28.537
No peripheral... Ah!

810
00:46:28.671 --> 00:46:31.173
The lizard-looking ones
can't climb for shit.

811
00:46:31.305 --> 00:46:34.843
The amphibian-looking ones like to
hide. lure ya in. eat ya whole.

812
00:46:34.977 --> 00:46:37.245
<b>- [GRUNTS]
- Then there are the Sandgobblers.</b>

813
00:46:37.379 --> 00:46:39.014
Those guys are badasses.

814
00:46:39.147 --> 00:46:41.049
Badasses!

815
00:46:41.182 --> 00:46:43.017
Yeah. I know.
I fell into their hole.

816
00:46:43.151 --> 00:46:44.787
What you saw were worker bees.

817
00:46:44.919 --> 00:46:48.490
What you wanna avoid under
all circumstances is a queen.

818
00:46:48.624 --> 00:46:50.292
How do I know if it's a queen?

819
00:46:50.424 --> 00:46:54.363
Well. your first clue would be a
giant fin slicing through the earth.

820
00:46:54.497 --> 00:46:57.667
following every single sound
and vibration you make.

821
00:46:57.799 --> 00:46:59.702
<b>- You howling in pain...
- [SHRIEKS]</b>

822
00:46:59.834 --> 00:47:02.837
...as you're being ripped
in half will be your second.

823
00:47:02.971 --> 00:47:05.740
<b>- [GROANS]
- Copy. I'll keep that in mind.</b>

824
00:47:05.874 --> 00:47:09.377
<b>CLYDE: Well. we're getting
close to where our paths diverge.</b>

825
00:47:09.511 --> 00:47:12.982
You're gonna wanna go west
to Jenner. the beaches.

826
00:47:13.115 --> 00:47:16.752
Or you can be sensible.
come with us to the mountains.

827
00:47:17.718 --> 00:47:21.155
Yeah. um. I think I've been
sensible all my life.

828
00:47:21.288 --> 00:47:22.892
and it's really
gotten me nowhere.

829
00:47:23.024 --> 00:47:25.593
Come with us.
Strength in numbers. you know?

830
00:47:26.462 --> 00:47:28.464
Besides.
think we'd make a good team.

831
00:47:28.596 --> 00:47:30.799
No. I think so. too.
I just. uh...

832
00:47:31.533 --> 00:47:32.935
It's just something I gotta do.

833
00:47:33.067 --> 00:47:35.037
It's not fair.

834
00:47:35.169 --> 00:47:37.772
Wh... Hey. Wha...

835
00:47:37.906 --> 00:47:41.176
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
Whoa. whoa. What's going on?

836
00:47:41.310 --> 00:47:43.279
Why do you gotta go?

837
00:47:45.046 --> 00:47:48.216
'Cause this girl. she means a lot to me.
You know?

838
00:47:48.350 --> 00:47:52.321
Come on. You know I gotta do this.
We talked about this.

839
00:47:53.522 --> 00:47:56.024
Hey. you know what?
I got something for ya.

840
00:47:56.158 --> 00:47:58.560
I don't even know if you'd know
what this is. but...

841
00:47:58.694 --> 00:47:59.995
Lipstick?

842
00:48:00.127 --> 00:48:01.162
Oh.

843
00:48:01.296 --> 00:48:03.097
<b>- [LAUGHS] What?
- Yeah.</b>

844
00:48:03.232 --> 00:48:05.500
<b>- [GIGGLES]
- Yeah. it's lip...</b>

845
00:48:05.633 --> 00:48:06.935
Aw.

846
00:48:08.669 --> 00:48:11.038
I take back what I said before.

847
00:48:11.173 --> 00:48:12.808
Aimee's gonna love you.

848
00:48:14.375 --> 00:48:16.477
Thanks. Minnow.
You got some snot.

849
00:48:16.611 --> 00:48:19.014
<b>- [LAUGHS] Yeah.
- [JOEL CHUCKLES]</b>

850
00:48:19.881 --> 00:48:22.450
All right. Come on.

851
00:48:28.323 --> 00:48:29.892
Final lesson.

852
00:48:31.660 --> 00:48:33.228
Listen to your instincts
out here.

853
00:48:33.361 --> 00:48:34.829
They'll keep you alive.

854
00:48:34.964 --> 00:48:38.634
Yeah. What if I have.
uh. terrible instincts?

855
00:48:38.767 --> 00:48:39.801
You'll die.

856
00:48:40.334 --> 00:48:41.769
Y...

857
00:48:41.903 --> 00:48:46.006
Listen. man. good instincts
are earned by making mistakes.

858
00:48:46.975 --> 00:48:49.177
If you're lucky enough
to survive a few mistakes.

859
00:48:49.310 --> 00:48:51.546
you're gonna be okay out here.

860
00:48:53.482 --> 00:48:55.217
This might come in handy. too.

861
00:48:55.350 --> 00:48:56.718
Wow!

862
00:48:57.586 --> 00:48:58.962
Oh. that's great.
Do you have. uh...

863
00:48:58.986 --> 00:49:00.721
Do you have any more
that I could have?

864
00:49:00.856 --> 00:49:01.890
You get one.

865
00:49:02.024 --> 00:49:06.127
Pull the pin. count to five.
Not four. not six.

866
00:49:06.261 --> 00:49:07.861
Five.

867
00:49:07.995 --> 00:49:09.365
Got it.

868
00:49:12.734 --> 00:49:14.036
You're gonna be okay.

869
00:49:15.870 --> 00:49:16.870
Minnow?

870
00:49:16.971 --> 00:49:18.406
Let's go. kid.

871
00:49:21.575 --> 00:49:24.813
Hey. man. you made it
all this way from Fairfield.

872
00:49:25.714 --> 00:49:28.084
What's another 30 miles. huh?

873
00:49:36.892 --> 00:49:38.125
<b>[BOY BARKING]</b>

874
00:49:38.260 --> 00:49:40.127
<b>CLYDE: Uh-oh. here he comes.</b>

875
00:49:40.261 --> 00:49:41.997
<b>- Hi.
- [CLYDE CHUCKLES]</b>

876
00:49:44.299 --> 00:49:45.701
Hey there.

877
00:49:56.444 --> 00:49:58.513
<b>[BOY WHINES]</b>

878
00:49:58.647 --> 00:50:00.749
I know.
I'm gonna miss 'em. too.

879
00:50:00.883 --> 00:50:03.350
It's a good decision.
though. It's good.

880
00:50:03.484 --> 00:50:05.720
You feel good about it. right?

881
00:50:08.624 --> 00:50:10.058
Come on. Boy.

882
00:50:11.959 --> 00:50:16.598
<b>[WHINING]</b>

883
00:50:33.515 --> 00:50:37.420
<b>[NO AUDIBLE DIALOGUE]</b>

884
00:50:45.660 --> 00:50:48.029
Aw. I'm okay.
I'm just gonna...

885
00:50:49.031 --> 00:50:50.666
You can have that.

886
00:50:51.566 --> 00:50:53.434
I'll just stick to the beans.

887
00:50:53.567 --> 00:50:54.703
<b>- I'm good.
- [WHINES]</b>

888
00:50:54.837 --> 00:50:57.139
I'm not gonna eat that. so...

889
00:51:14.089 --> 00:51:16.157
Hey. come on.
We gotta keep moving.

890
00:51:16.290 --> 00:51:19.828
I know. There's a lot
of creepy stuff. Creepy boats.

891
00:51:21.296 --> 00:51:22.864
Kind of a creepy sign.

892
00:51:22.997 --> 00:51:26.067
But nothing
we haven't seen before.

893
00:51:26.200 --> 00:51:27.468
Just gotta be brave.

894
00:51:27.602 --> 00:51:29.637
<b>- [BOY WHINES]
- What...</b>

895
00:51:30.939 --> 00:51:33.575
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
What's going on? What's happening?

896
00:51:33.707 --> 00:51:34.776
<b>- You okay?
- [BARKS]</b>

897
00:51:34.910 --> 00:51:37.513
<b>- You hearing something. Boy?
- [BARKS]</b>

898
00:51:37.645 --> 00:51:40.015
Boy. Boy. Boy! Boy!

899
00:51:42.084 --> 00:51:45.185
Hey! Boy! Boy! Boy!

900
00:51:45.319 --> 00:51:46.854
<b>- Boy! Are you okay?
- [WHINES]</b>

901
00:51:46.988 --> 00:51:49.058
I need some kind
of communication here.

902
00:51:49.191 --> 00:51:51.160
<b>[CHITTERING. FAINT]</b>

903
00:51:51.292 --> 00:51:54.028
Oh. I hear it.

904
00:51:54.162 --> 00:51:57.198
<b>[CHITTERING CONTINUES]</b>

905
00:52:05.140 --> 00:52:06.374
We gotta go. Hey.

906
00:52:06.508 --> 00:52:10.245
We really gotta go.
Please get out from under the duck.

907
00:52:11.011 --> 00:52:13.147
<b>[RUMBLING]</b>

908
00:52:19.488 --> 00:52:20.990
<b>[WHISPERS]
We gotta go.</b>

909
00:52:25.526 --> 00:52:29.163
<b>[HIGH-PITCHED WARBLING]</b>

910
00:52:43.544 --> 00:52:45.580
<b>[WARBLING STOPS]</b>

911
00:52:58.127 --> 00:52:59.228
<b>[BOY WHINES]</b>

912
00:53:01.196 --> 00:53:02.565
<b>[BOY BARKS]</b>

913
00:53:06.635 --> 00:53:08.337
<b>[BOY BARKS]</b>

914
00:53:18.814 --> 00:53:21.250
<i><b>WOMAN: Joel. You okay?</b></i>

915
00:53:22.484 --> 00:53:23.886
You okay?

916
00:53:24.718 --> 00:53:26.487
Joel! Get out of the car!

917
00:53:27.089 --> 00:53:28.523
<i>Joel. get outta the car!</i>

918
00:53:28.656 --> 00:53:32.127
<b>- [PEOPLE SCREAMING]
- [GASPING]</b>

919
00:53:32.260 --> 00:53:33.962
Run. Joel. run!

920
00:53:34.095 --> 00:53:36.030
<i>Run! Go!</i>

921
00:53:40.569 --> 00:53:41.837
<i><b>MOTHER: You can survive this.</b></i>

922
00:53:41.970 --> 00:53:45.107
<b>[ECHOING]
I love you. I love you.</b>

923
00:53:53.680 --> 00:53:55.917
<b>- [THUDDING]
- [GASPS]</b>

924
00:53:58.453 --> 00:54:01.357
<b>[BARKING. WHINING]</b>

925
00:54:07.095 --> 00:54:08.663
No.

926
00:54:12.399 --> 00:54:13.735
Hey!

927
00:54:14.468 --> 00:54:16.371
<b>[SHRIEKING. ROARING]</b>

928
00:54:32.587 --> 00:54:34.823
<b>- [WHINING]
- Boy?</b>

929
00:54:37.359 --> 00:54:39.028
Are you okay?

930
00:54:40.595 --> 00:54:42.096
<b>[BARKING]</b>

931
00:54:42.229 --> 00:54:43.865
Yeah! Yeah. you're okay!
You're okay!

932
00:54:43.999 --> 00:54:47.435
You're okay.
You're okay. You're okay.

933
00:54:47.569 --> 00:54:49.204
Aren't you? Aren't you?

934
00:54:49.337 --> 00:54:51.039
Ah!

935
00:54:51.173 --> 00:54:52.374
Yeah!

936
00:54:53.741 --> 00:54:55.244
We're monster killers.

937
00:54:55.377 --> 00:54:58.413
<b>- [THUNDER RUMBLING. CRASHING]
- Whoo-ooh!</b>

938
00:55:04.319 --> 00:55:05.721
<b>Ah!
[LAUGHS]</b>

939
00:55:08.290 --> 00:55:10.159
<b>[SIGHS]</b>

940
00:55:11.225 --> 00:55:12.794
Wow.

941
00:55:12.928 --> 00:55:15.497
You know. I haven't felt
the rain in seven years.

942
00:55:15.631 --> 00:55:18.133
Pretty cool.
Pretty cool.

943
00:55:22.770 --> 00:55:25.006
Hey. Boy.
you think I'm crazy?

944
00:55:26.540 --> 00:55:28.309
Coming all this way?

945
00:55:31.011 --> 00:55:33.048
<b>[FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE]
Hello.</b>

946
00:55:35.783 --> 00:55:37.352
<b>[BOY GROWLS]</b>

947
00:55:42.591 --> 00:55:46.729
<b>[ELECTRONIC WHIRRING. BEEPING]</b>

948
00:55:50.765 --> 00:55:52.500
Holy shit.

949
00:55:54.836 --> 00:55:56.571
You're alive.

950
00:55:56.705 --> 00:55:59.374
I mean... you're on.

951
00:55:59.506 --> 00:56:04.779
I have 51 minutes of power left.
What is your name?

952
00:56:04.912 --> 00:56:07.481
Uh. I'm Joel.

953
00:56:08.216 --> 00:56:10.852
- My name is Joel.
- Hello. Joel.

954
00:56:10.986 --> 00:56:13.421
I am so pleased to meet you.

955
00:56:13.555 --> 00:56:15.123
My name is Mavis.

956
00:56:15.256 --> 00:56:17.258
But if you were to write it out.

957
00:56:17.392 --> 00:56:20.261
you would write it
with a 1 and not an I.

958
00:56:20.395 --> 00:56:22.063
Yeah. I know.

959
00:56:22.196 --> 00:56:26.066
You are familiar with the Mav1s line.
Delightful!

960
00:56:26.200 --> 00:56:28.602
You guys were supposed to be
the next amazing thing.

961
00:56:28.736 --> 00:56:30.439
I can't believe
I'm talkin' to one.

962
00:56:30.571 --> 00:56:32.307
But if you were to write it out.

963
00:56:32.441 --> 00:56:35.544
you would write it
with a 1 and not an I.

964
00:56:36.910 --> 00:56:39.079
Yeah. You said that.

965
00:56:39.714 --> 00:56:42.049
Years ago. I was bitten in half

966
00:56:42.182 --> 00:56:45.419
by something
I did not get a chance to name.

967
00:56:45.553 --> 00:56:48.356
I crawled here for safety
and powered down.

968
00:56:48.490 --> 00:56:51.725
hoping someone
would one day find me.

969
00:56:51.859 --> 00:56:54.194
And here you are!

970
00:56:54.328 --> 00:56:55.162
Amazing.

971
00:56:55.296 --> 00:56:57.732
Joel. besides
conversing with me.

972
00:56:57.865 --> 00:56:59.600
for which
I am eternally grateful.

973
00:56:59.734 --> 00:57:03.537
may I ask what you are doing
outside of your colony?

974
00:57:03.671 --> 00:57:04.671
Yeah. um...

975
00:57:04.738 --> 00:57:07.375
Did you steal food?

976
00:57:07.508 --> 00:57:08.742
No.

977
00:57:08.875 --> 00:57:10.410
No. I didn't steal any food.

978
00:57:10.544 --> 00:57:14.883
Um. I'm actually on a quest...
to find a girl.

979
00:57:15.015 --> 00:57:18.952
Why. Joel. a lovely lady
has caught your eye!

980
00:57:19.087 --> 00:57:20.321
What is her name?

981
00:57:20.455 --> 00:57:24.259
Uh. her name's Aimee.
With one I and two E's.

982
00:57:24.392 --> 00:57:28.430
She sounds like
an incredible person. Joel.

983
00:57:29.832 --> 00:57:32.600
Is there anything
I can do to assist you

984
00:57:32.734 --> 00:57:36.371
in your quest for Aimee
with one I and two E's?

985
00:57:36.504 --> 00:57:41.243
Nope. Appreciate it. Mav1s.
but. uh. unfortunately not.

986
00:57:41.375 --> 00:57:45.214
Unless you happen to have a power
source to an SK-21 ham radio handy.

987
00:57:46.915 --> 00:57:48.283
Oh. no. but...

988
00:57:48.415 --> 00:57:51.685
I would be honored to donate
my remaining power to you

989
00:57:51.819 --> 00:57:56.258
if it would help you with your quest
for Aimee with one I and two E's.

990
00:57:56.390 --> 00:57:57.925
<b>[CHUCKLES]</b>

991
00:58:01.330 --> 00:58:04.098
She probably thinks
I've been devoured by now.

992
00:58:04.232 --> 00:58:06.902
Oh. this is all so exciting!

993
00:58:07.769 --> 00:58:09.069
<b>[STATIC]</b>

994
00:58:09.203 --> 00:58:11.440
- It's working.
- Hooray!

995
00:58:12.573 --> 00:58:14.975
3022? Come in. 3022.

996
00:58:15.109 --> 00:58:17.312
<i><b>- AIMEE: Joel?
- Aimee! Hey. Hey.</b></i>

997
00:58:17.444 --> 00:58:19.881
<i>Your colony told me you were
coming here. Are you okay?</i>

998
00:58:20.015 --> 00:58:22.484
<i>I was worried.
It's so good to hear your voice.</i>

999
00:58:22.616 --> 00:58:26.053
Yeah. it's good to hear yours. too.
Yeah. I'm alive. I'm good. I'm okay.

1000
00:58:26.187 --> 00:58:28.856
<i>I-I-I can't believe
you're actually doing this.</i>

1001
00:58:28.990 --> 00:58:32.026
I know. It's crazy. Aimee.
I cannot wait to tell you everything.

1002
00:58:32.160 --> 00:58:33.962
I feel like a whole new man.
you know?

1003
00:58:34.095 --> 00:58:36.397
You should see me out here.
I'm fighting monsters.

1004
00:58:36.531 --> 00:58:38.799
I'm in a motel right now
with a robot and a dog.

1005
00:58:38.933 --> 00:58:41.135
<i>What? That sounds crazy.</i>

1006
00:58:41.269 --> 00:58:43.404
<i>How far are you
from Jenner Beach?</i>

1007
00:58:43.537 --> 00:58:47.074
Um. how far? I'm getting close.
I'm. um...

1008
00:58:48.042 --> 00:58:49.410
I'm 9.3 miles to you.

1009
00:58:49.544 --> 00:58:52.480
<i>Joel. listen.
I have amazing news.</i>

1010
00:58:52.613 --> 00:58:55.816
<i>Some survivors showed up a few days
ago. and they're rescuing us.</i>

1011
00:58:55.950 --> 00:58:57.284
<i>They're gonna get us
out of here!</i>

1012
00:58:57.417 --> 00:58:59.820
<i>They're really helping me
with the colony.</i>

1013
00:58:59.953 --> 00:59:02.591
Oh. Okay. g-getting you out
of there? What do you mean?

1014
00:59:02.723 --> 00:59:06.227
<i>I can't remember the last time I actually
felt like everything was going to be...</i>

1015
00:59:06.694 --> 00:59:08.462
Wh... Aimee?

1016
00:59:08.595 --> 00:59:09.897
Aimee? Aimee?

1017
00:59:10.031 --> 00:59:11.133
Shit.

1018
00:59:11.265 --> 00:59:13.968
My battery
has automatically shut down

1019
00:59:14.102 --> 00:59:18.640
in order to preserve
my final 15 minutes of power.

1020
00:59:18.772 --> 00:59:21.843
- I am very sorry. Joel.
- No. it's okay. Mav1s.

1021
00:59:21.975 --> 00:59:23.912
<b>- You don't have to...
- [THUNDER RUMBLING]</b>

1022
00:59:24.044 --> 00:59:26.313
<b>[ELECTRONIC HUMMING]</b>

1023
00:59:26.448 --> 00:59:27.882
Joel?

1024
00:59:28.015 --> 00:59:31.918
I haven't been outside
in a very long time.

1025
00:59:32.053 --> 00:59:34.288
Yeah. I hadn't. either.

1026
00:59:37.392 --> 00:59:38.660
<b>[WHINES]</b>

1027
00:59:40.261 --> 00:59:43.698
- There you go.
- Is something troubling you. Joel?

1028
00:59:43.832 --> 00:59:47.969
You can tell me anything.
as I am an empathetic listener.

1029
00:59:48.102 --> 00:59:54.308
Also. my memory banks will be
permanently erased in 14 minutes.

1030
00:59:56.144 --> 01:00:00.113
You know that feeling where you just
completely put yourself out there?

1031
01:00:00.247 --> 01:00:01.849
You know?
And you're so sure of it.

1032
01:00:01.982 --> 01:00:05.787
And... right when you're
about to cross the finish line.

1033
01:00:05.921 --> 01:00:10.857
you just think is this the dumbest...
thing I ever could've done?

1034
01:00:10.991 --> 01:00:13.627
I don't think it's dumb. Joel.

1035
01:00:13.761 --> 01:00:15.963
I think it's romantic.

1036
01:00:16.096 --> 01:00:18.466
Right. see?
Yeah. okay. you get it.

1037
01:00:19.433 --> 01:00:21.269
Romantic. that's what...
Yeah.

1038
01:00:21.401 --> 01:00:24.571
Do not give up
on your quest. Joel.

1039
01:00:24.705 --> 01:00:29.010
When you see her. she will
appreciate the grand romantic gesture

1040
01:00:29.144 --> 01:00:30.778
implied by your journey

1041
01:00:30.910 --> 01:00:34.849
and be moved by your kindness
and leadership qualities.

1042
01:00:34.982 --> 01:00:36.218
Thanks. Mav1s.

1043
01:00:37.651 --> 01:00:41.988
Another option is that Aimee will
not see those qualities in you

1044
01:00:42.122 --> 01:00:44.325
and you will have traveled
a great distance

1045
01:00:44.457 --> 01:00:47.294
only to be met
with disappointment.

1046
01:00:47.428 --> 01:00:51.532
Perhaps you will have learned
valuable lessons along the way?

1047
01:00:52.033 --> 01:00:53.534
Okay.

1048
01:00:53.667 --> 01:00:57.337
A third option is that you
don't survive the journey at all

1049
01:00:57.471 --> 01:00:59.573
and get eaten
by mutated insects...

1050
01:00:59.707 --> 01:01:01.541
- Okay. that's... I get it.
- ...amphibians...

1051
01:01:01.676 --> 01:01:04.011
There are so many ways
you could perish.

1052
01:01:04.145 --> 01:01:05.145
I get it.

1053
01:01:05.245 --> 01:01:07.548
Thanks for the...

1054
01:01:08.015 --> 01:01:09.417
Thanks for that.

1055
01:01:11.252 --> 01:01:13.688
Would you like
to see a trick. Joel?

1056
01:01:13.821 --> 01:01:15.222
Sure.

1057
01:01:15.356 --> 01:01:18.459
What is your full name.
and where were you born?

1058
01:01:18.593 --> 01:01:21.163
Uh. Joel Dawson.
Fairfield. California.

1059
01:01:24.131 --> 01:01:25.566
Whoa.

1060
01:01:27.102 --> 01:01:28.136
Whoa.

1061
01:01:28.269 --> 01:01:31.205
What lovely parents
you had. Joel.

1062
01:01:32.207 --> 01:01:34.076
Oh. my God.

1063
01:01:34.709 --> 01:01:35.743
Wow.

1064
01:01:36.477 --> 01:01:38.512
I don't even have a picture.

1065
01:01:38.645 --> 01:01:41.982
What would you say
to your mother now. Joel.

1066
01:01:42.116 --> 01:01:44.219
if you had the chance?

1067
01:01:50.457 --> 01:01:52.493
I guess I'd tell her I'm okay.

1068
01:01:57.231 --> 01:01:59.468
<i>I made it to a colony.</i>

1069
01:02:00.435 --> 01:02:03.772
Met a lot of really.
really good people

1070
01:02:03.904 --> 01:02:06.475
who took really good care of me.

1071
01:02:13.948 --> 01:02:16.217
They also lost a lot. so...

1072
01:02:18.986 --> 01:02:21.322
And I miss you guys so much.

1073
01:02:26.127 --> 01:02:27.529
I'm so sorry.

1074
01:02:35.937 --> 01:02:38.239
<b>[FAINT HUMMING. CHIRPING]</b>

1075
01:02:38.372 --> 01:02:41.509
Oh. look! Sky Jellies!

1076
01:02:41.642 --> 01:02:45.413
They're harmless
and quite lovely.

1077
01:02:46.613 --> 01:02:47.781
Wow.

1078
01:02:48.982 --> 01:02:51.819
<i>Oh! Canis familiaris!</i>

1079
01:02:51.953 --> 01:02:55.223
You found my foot.
Thank you.

1080
01:02:55.357 --> 01:02:58.627
- That's my dog.
- He's delightful.

1081
01:03:00.461 --> 01:03:02.464
Yeah. he's a good boy.

1082
01:03:03.732 --> 01:03:07.469
<b>- Joel. would you like to hear a song?
- [HUMMING. CHIRPING CONTINUE]</b>

1083
01:03:08.069 --> 01:03:09.571
Yeah. okay.

1084
01:03:09.703 --> 01:03:12.406
<b>[MAV1S PLAYING
"STAND BY ME" BY BEN E. KING]</b>

1085
01:03:20.881 --> 01:03:24.618
<i>♪ When the night has come ♪</i>

1086
01:03:26.421 --> 01:03:28.955
<i>♪ And the land is dark ♪</i>

1087
01:03:29.089 --> 01:03:30.792
<i>♪ And the moon ♪</i>

1088
01:03:30.926 --> 01:03:35.297
<i>♪ Is the only light we'll see ♪</i>

1089
01:03:36.564 --> 01:03:37.564
<b>[SONG CONTINUES. FAINT]</b>

1090
01:03:37.665 --> 01:03:38.825
You know. nature's kinda nice

1091
01:03:38.933 --> 01:03:40.968
when there's nothing trying
to kill you.

1092
01:03:41.102 --> 01:03:44.705
<i>♪ Oh. I won't be afraid ♪</i>

1093
01:03:44.839 --> 01:03:45.874
<b>[SONG STOPS]</b>

1094
01:03:48.577 --> 01:03:49.711
Mav1s?

1095
01:03:55.182 --> 01:03:56.650
Thanks.

1096
01:04:02.423 --> 01:04:04.859
<i><b>JOEL: Some survivors showed up at the camp.</b></i>

1097
01:04:06.160 --> 01:04:08.929
That's not something I gotta worry
about. you don't think. right?

1098
01:04:09.062 --> 01:04:11.799
I mean. what are the odds
that they're. like. awesome

1099
01:04:11.932 --> 01:04:16.136
and similar to my age and potentially
a threat to me romantically?

1100
01:04:16.270 --> 01:04:18.171
Slim to none. probably.

1101
01:04:18.305 --> 01:04:21.375
I think it's good. actually.
I think we're totally. uh... fine.

1102
01:04:21.508 --> 01:04:24.645
Actually. why don't we pick up the
pace a little bit. just in case...

1103
01:04:26.147 --> 01:04:27.449
Um...

1104
01:04:28.348 --> 01:04:30.218
Okay. you know what?

1105
01:04:30.350 --> 01:04:32.354
Why don't we go
another way. Yeah?

1106
01:04:33.787 --> 01:04:34.955
Uh...

1107
01:04:38.292 --> 01:04:39.292
Boy?

1108
01:04:39.359 --> 01:04:40.595
Boy!

1109
01:04:42.229 --> 01:04:44.098
Boy. where you going?

1110
01:04:44.232 --> 01:04:47.836
<b>- [RUMBLING]
- [BRANCHES CRACKING]</b>

1111
01:04:55.676 --> 01:04:57.379
Queen.

1112
01:05:05.285 --> 01:05:06.520
<b>[SQUEAKS]</b>

1113
01:05:16.464 --> 01:05:17.832
<b>[SQUEAKS]</b>

1114
01:05:17.964 --> 01:05:19.968
<b>[CHITTERING. GROWLING]</b>

1115
01:05:23.236 --> 01:05:26.273
<b>[GASPING]</b>

1116
01:05:26.406 --> 01:05:28.008
Run. Boy! Run!

1117
01:05:28.142 --> 01:05:29.678
<b>- [BOY YIPS]
- Get...</b>

1118
01:05:31.312 --> 01:05:33.548
<b>- Go. go! Go!
- [YIPPING CONTINUES]</b>

1119
01:05:35.982 --> 01:05:37.017
<b>[GASPS]</b>

1120
01:05:39.687 --> 01:05:40.820
Sh...

1121
01:05:41.388 --> 01:05:43.792
<b>- [GASPS]
- [BARKING]</b>

1122
01:05:45.125 --> 01:05:46.861
<b>[SHOUTS]
Wait!</b>

1123
01:05:46.993 --> 01:05:48.229
Boy!

1124
01:05:48.361 --> 01:05:50.798
<b>Boy. I can't run that fast!
[GASPING]</b>

1125
01:05:55.169 --> 01:05:56.871
<b>[GROANING]</b>

1126
01:05:57.004 --> 01:05:58.540
<b>[BARKING. WHIMPERING]</b>

1127
01:06:06.846 --> 01:06:09.450
<b>- Shh-shh-shh-shh-shh-shh-shh.
- [WHINES SOFTLY]</b>

1128
01:06:27.468 --> 01:06:30.904
<b>[ROARING. SHRIEKING]</b>

1129
01:06:31.038 --> 01:06:32.774
Shh-shh-shh. Shh.

1130
01:06:33.674 --> 01:06:35.910
<b>[WHINES SOFTLY]</b>

1131
01:06:36.044 --> 01:06:39.114
Shh. Shh. shh. shh. shh.

1132
01:06:57.165 --> 01:07:00.668
<b>[GROWLS]</b>

1133
01:07:08.408 --> 01:07:11.712
Oh. my God. Oh. I'm so sorry.

1134
01:07:12.212 --> 01:07:13.580
I'm sorry.

1135
01:07:17.919 --> 01:07:19.754
<b>[WHISPERS]
What are you doing?</b>

1136
01:07:20.955 --> 01:07:22.323
Don't you dare.

1137
01:07:22.457 --> 01:07:25.093
<b>- Whoa. whoa. What are you doing?
- [YIPS]</b>

1138
01:07:27.560 --> 01:07:29.096
No. Wait. Boy!

1139
01:07:29.229 --> 01:07:30.564
Boy!

1140
01:07:31.533 --> 01:07:33.734
<b>- [WHIMPERS]
- Boy. don't even think about it.</b>

1141
01:07:33.868 --> 01:07:35.502
Don't. Don't you do it.

1142
01:07:35.636 --> 01:07:37.638
<b>- Don't. Don't. No!
- [BARKS]</b>

1143
01:07:37.770 --> 01:07:39.038
<b>- [GRUNTS]
- [BARKING CONTINUES]</b>

1144
01:07:39.173 --> 01:07:41.209
<b>[QUEEN CHITTERING]</b>

1145
01:07:44.245 --> 01:07:46.681
<b>[GRUNTING]</b>

1146
01:07:50.151 --> 01:07:51.853
Count to five.

1147
01:07:53.220 --> 01:07:54.589
One. two...

1148
01:07:58.825 --> 01:08:00.994
Two. Uh. three. four...

1149
01:08:01.129 --> 01:08:02.529
five!

1150
01:08:14.508 --> 01:08:17.044
<b>[GASPING]</b>

1151
01:08:19.146 --> 01:08:20.481
<b>[HOT DOG SQUEAKS]</b>

1152
01:08:21.982 --> 01:08:23.950
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

1153
01:08:24.083 --> 01:08:25.586
Yes!

1154
01:08:25.718 --> 01:08:28.056
Yes! Oh. my God!

1155
01:08:29.123 --> 01:08:30.857
Oh. that was awesome.

1156
01:08:30.990 --> 01:08:33.392
<b>I feel like Tom Cruise.
[GASPS]</b>

1157
01:08:33.526 --> 01:08:35.596
<b>[LAUGHS]</b>

1158
01:08:35.729 --> 01:08:39.098
<b>[GRUNTS] Oh! Ow.
What the hell is...</b>

1159
01:08:39.232 --> 01:08:40.802
<b>[GROANS]
Ow!</b>

1160
01:08:47.342 --> 01:08:49.610
<b>Ow!
[GROANS]</b>

1161
01:08:49.744 --> 01:08:52.413
<b>[GASPING. PANTING]</b>

1162
01:08:52.547 --> 01:08:54.281
Oh. my God.

1163
01:08:55.216 --> 01:08:56.284
Ow! Ow!

1164
01:08:59.020 --> 01:09:01.254
Get that dress out of my face!

1165
01:09:01.387 --> 01:09:03.390
<b>[GRUNTING]</b>

1166
01:09:03.524 --> 01:09:05.258
Boy?

1167
01:09:05.392 --> 01:09:06.793
<b>[GROANS]</b>

1168
01:09:08.294 --> 01:09:11.199
<b>[GRUNTING CONTINUES]</b>

1169
01:09:15.069 --> 01:09:16.370
Oh!

1170
01:09:16.503 --> 01:09:17.905
<b>[GROANS]</b>

1171
01:09:22.409 --> 01:09:23.912
Oh. f...

1172
01:09:27.547 --> 01:09:30.784
<b>[GASPING. GAGGING]</b>

1173
01:09:36.190 --> 01:09:37.190
Okay.

1174
01:09:37.290 --> 01:09:38.892
Oh. no.

1175
01:09:42.428 --> 01:09:45.966
<b>[PANTING. SCREAMING]</b>

1176
01:09:57.144 --> 01:09:59.512
Okay. all right.
I think I'm good.

1177
01:09:59.646 --> 01:10:01.349
I think I got 'em all.

1178
01:10:02.350 --> 01:10:04.218
What?

1179
01:10:04.351 --> 01:10:06.521
<b>[GROANING]</b>

1180
01:10:06.654 --> 01:10:09.524
<b>God! No!
[GRUNTING]</b>

1181
01:10:09.656 --> 01:10:12.659
<b>[SCREAMING. GASPING]</b>

1182
01:10:13.360 --> 01:10:15.296
<b>[SHOUTING]
You! You! You!</b>

1183
01:10:15.428 --> 01:10:18.432
This is all your fault!
What is wrong with you?

1184
01:10:18.565 --> 01:10:21.001
Why don't you listen to me.
huh? Huh?

1185
01:10:21.135 --> 01:10:23.412
You have any idea what you just did?
You just almost got us killed!

1186
01:10:23.436 --> 01:10:26.106
We are supposed to care
about each other. okay?

1187
01:10:26.239 --> 01:10:29.943
I would never do that to you. never!
You bailed on me! Oh. my God!

1188
01:10:30.077 --> 01:10:33.113
That freakin' dress!
I can't take it anymore!

1189
01:10:33.247 --> 01:10:34.615
<b>[GROWLS]</b>

1190
01:10:44.557 --> 01:10:45.792
<b>[GROANS]</b>

1191
01:10:46.793 --> 01:10:48.896
<b>[ROCK BALLAD PLAYING]</b>

1192
01:10:49.030 --> 01:10:52.033
<i><b>MAN: ♪ Think I'm coming down ♪</b></i>

1193
01:10:52.165 --> 01:10:54.534
<i><b>JOEL: Dear Aimee. It's not looking good.</b></i>

1194
01:10:54.668 --> 01:10:56.828
<i>And by "it." I don't remember
what I was talking about.</i>

1195
01:10:56.937 --> 01:10:58.538
<i>♪ Coming down ♪</i>

1196
01:10:58.672 --> 01:11:01.042
<i>I can't feel my feet.</i>

1197
01:11:01.174 --> 01:11:02.243
<i>Or my face.</i>

1198
01:11:02.375 --> 01:11:04.211
<i><b>- ♪ Coming down ♪
- [SCREAMS]</b></i>

1199
01:11:04.343 --> 01:11:05.479
<i>I think I'm dying.</i>

1200
01:11:05.613 --> 01:11:11.351
<i>♪ You know
I think I'm coming down ♪</i>

1201
01:11:13.186 --> 01:11:15.888
<b>[WHIMPERS]</b>

1202
01:11:16.022 --> 01:11:20.761
<i><b>MINNOW: I'm gonna kill you. Joel Dawson!
I'm gonna eat you like broccoli!</b></i>

1203
01:11:22.061 --> 01:11:24.464
<i><b>CLYDE: Ferns like these have an antivenom.</b></i>

1204
01:11:24.597 --> 01:11:28.068
<i><b>- Good in a pinch for snakes. slugs.
- [GASPING]</b></i>

1205
01:11:39.646 --> 01:11:41.883
<b>[WHIMPERING CONTINUES]</b>

1206
01:11:42.615 --> 01:11:44.185
<b>[GASPS]</b>

1207
01:11:53.427 --> 01:11:55.262
<b>[BELLS JINGLING. CLANGING]</b>

1208
01:11:55.396 --> 01:11:58.299
<i><b>JOEL: If you find the best dog ever.</b></i>

1209
01:11:58.431 --> 01:11:59.900
<i>that's Boy.</i>

1210
01:12:00.802 --> 01:12:02.936
<i>Please. look after him.</i>

1211
01:12:03.537 --> 01:12:05.039
<i>Tell him I'm sorry.</i>

1212
01:12:05.172 --> 01:12:07.317
<i><b>- [WHISPERING] Have you seen my dog?
- Tell him I love him.</b></i>

1213
01:12:07.341 --> 01:12:09.810
Have you seen him?
I yelled at him.

1214
01:12:09.944 --> 01:12:12.389
<i>And don't take his dress out of his mouth.
He doesn't like that.</i>

1215
01:12:12.413 --> 01:12:14.281
And now I might not
ever see him again.

1216
01:12:14.414 --> 01:12:17.484
<i>And please don't shout at him.
I know you won't.</i>

1217
01:12:20.154 --> 01:12:21.321
Joel.

1218
01:12:22.589 --> 01:12:24.056
Oh. my God.

1219
01:12:24.591 --> 01:12:26.894
- It's you.
- Aimee?

1220
01:12:27.028 --> 01:12:29.363
I can't believe you made it.

1221
01:12:29.495 --> 01:12:32.399
Oh. my God.
I can't believe you made it.

1222
01:12:32.531 --> 01:12:34.267
You made it. Joel.

1223
01:12:34.901 --> 01:12:37.739
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. yeah.

1224
01:12:39.806 --> 01:12:41.708
Oh. you're so beautiful.

1225
01:12:42.743 --> 01:12:47.981
<i><b>WOMAN: ♪ Tears in waves
Minds on fire ♪</b></i>

1226
01:12:49.982 --> 01:12:55.155
<i>♪ Nights alone by your side ♪</i>

1227
01:12:56.890 --> 01:12:58.459
That was nice.

1228
01:13:01.762 --> 01:13:06.801
[SONG PLAYING ON SPEAKER]

1229
01:13:12.606 --> 01:13:13.841
Aimee?

1230
01:13:15.877 --> 01:13:16.877
Aimee.

1231
01:13:16.944 --> 01:13:18.646
- Aimee.
- Hey. hey. hey. hey.

1232
01:13:18.779 --> 01:13:20.280
T-T-Take it easy.
Take it easy.

1233
01:13:20.414 --> 01:13:23.785
Still pretty messed up from all the poison.
How do you feel?

1234
01:13:24.685 --> 01:13:26.053
I feel... I'm good.

1235
01:13:26.186 --> 01:13:28.354
Good. No. I'm f...
I-I'm okay.

1236
01:13:29.422 --> 01:13:32.558
What was it like? I mean.
you have to tell me everything.

1237
01:13:32.692 --> 01:13:35.762
Honestly. it wasn't that bad. I don't
know what everyone's complaining about.

1238
01:13:35.896 --> 01:13:38.431
- Oh?
- No. it was terrible.

1239
01:13:38.565 --> 01:13:40.466
I almost... died a lot.

1240
01:13:40.601 --> 01:13:41.735
<b>[LAUGHS]</b>

1241
01:13:41.869 --> 01:13:44.004
It's so good to see you.

1242
01:13:44.872 --> 01:13:46.673
I'm lucky you found me
when you did.

1243
01:13:46.806 --> 01:13:48.074
About that. um...

1244
01:13:48.208 --> 01:13:50.310
And hey. we... kissed.

1245
01:13:50.444 --> 01:13:53.481
- You were hallucinating pretty hard.
- How amazing was that. huh?

1246
01:13:53.614 --> 01:13:55.449
You kissed Old Pete.

1247
01:13:55.583 --> 01:13:58.286
- Hi. Pete.
- Oh. Yeah.

1248
01:13:58.418 --> 01:14:00.453
<b>[JOEL LAUGHS]</b>

1249
01:14:00.587 --> 01:14:02.156
That'd be hilarious.

1250
01:14:04.792 --> 01:14:06.294
Oh. yeah. I really did.

1251
01:14:08.995 --> 01:14:11.565
I don't know how
to move on from this.

1252
01:14:11.699 --> 01:14:13.799
What was that you said
on the radio about. uh...

1253
01:14:13.933 --> 01:14:17.437
Yeah. This yacht captain and his
crew show up out of the blue.

1254
01:14:17.571 --> 01:14:20.173
- Did you say a yacht captain?
- Yeah. yeah.

1255
01:14:20.306 --> 01:14:23.375
And he says he can find us a safe
place to live and a new home.

1256
01:14:23.510 --> 01:14:25.190
I'm trying to pack
everything up right now.

1257
01:14:25.311 --> 01:14:27.013
Why is he called
a yacht captain?

1258
01:14:27.146 --> 01:14:29.026
'Cause he's the captain
of the yacht. you moron.

1259
01:14:29.149 --> 01:14:31.519
Oh. my God.
Be nice. Bill.

1260
01:14:31.651 --> 01:14:33.419
- What?
- I'm trying to listen.

1261
01:14:33.553 --> 01:14:36.591
So anyway. I just wanted to say
something to you. though...

1262
01:14:36.723 --> 01:14:37.723
- Whoo.
- Oh!

1263
01:14:37.790 --> 01:14:39.159
<b>JANICE: Aimee! Aimee!</b>

1264
01:14:39.293 --> 01:14:41.395
We got another leak
in the main line.

1265
01:14:41.528 --> 01:14:44.097
Bastard's spitting freshwater
all over the beach!

1266
01:14:44.230 --> 01:14:46.999
Yeah. yeah. thank you. Janice.
I'll be right there.

1267
01:14:47.133 --> 01:14:48.734
- Oh.
- Hi. Joel.

1268
01:14:48.869 --> 01:14:50.804
Hey. Janice.
Good to meet you.

1269
01:14:50.937 --> 01:14:52.306
- Please...
- Everyone's so old.

1270
01:14:52.439 --> 01:14:54.976
<b>- [LAUGHS] You came at a crazy time.
- Yeah.</b>

1271
01:14:55.109 --> 01:14:57.111
- Can we put a pin in this?
- Yeah.

1272
01:14:57.244 --> 01:14:59.580
<b>[WHISPERS]
Put a pin in it. Sure.</b>

1273
01:15:16.963 --> 01:15:18.399
Hey. man.

1274
01:15:35.248 --> 01:15:37.317
<b>JANICE: It's all falling apart. Aimee.</b>

1275
01:15:37.450 --> 01:15:40.820
I don't know what's happening here.
What can we do?

1276
01:15:40.954 --> 01:15:44.024
<b>AIMEE: Yeah. I know. Janice.
I'm sorry.</b>

1277
01:15:44.158 --> 01:15:46.793
Janice. will you just...
Will you give me the wrench?

1278
01:15:47.660 --> 01:15:49.663
<b>- JANICE: This is a shitshow.
- [WAVE CRASHES]</b>

1279
01:15:49.796 --> 01:15:53.167
Who left the kelp out in the sun?
That was meant to be packed up already.

1280
01:15:53.299 --> 01:15:55.580
<b>- It's gonna bring in the flies.
- MAN: It's swellin' up.</b>

1281
01:15:55.636 --> 01:15:59.173
Yeah. I don't think feet
are meant to be that color.

1282
01:16:00.906 --> 01:16:01.906
Hey.

1283
01:16:01.975 --> 01:16:03.209
Perfect timing.

1284
01:16:03.343 --> 01:16:06.279
Guys! Joel.
this is Dana and Rocko.

1285
01:16:06.413 --> 01:16:08.915
- What's up?
- These are the guys from the yacht.

1286
01:16:09.048 --> 01:16:10.350
Cool. Oh.

1287
01:16:10.482 --> 01:16:12.886
Is that a...
Is that an arm cannon?

1288
01:16:13.019 --> 01:16:14.421
Homemade.

1289
01:16:14.553 --> 01:16:17.156
So which one...
which one of you is the yacht captain?

1290
01:16:17.289 --> 01:16:19.892
Guilty as charged.
Captain Brooks Wilkinson.

1291
01:16:20.026 --> 01:16:22.095
- Royal Australian Navy.
- Oh. dear God.

1292
01:16:22.229 --> 01:16:25.031
Retired. of course.
My mates call me Cap.

1293
01:16:25.164 --> 01:16:26.167
How you doing. man?

1294
01:16:26.299 --> 01:16:27.577
I see you've met
these specimens.

1295
01:16:27.601 --> 01:16:29.903
but this beautiful lady.
that's our yacht.

1296
01:16:30.904 --> 01:16:33.774
A little showy for my taste.
but she gets the job done.

1297
01:16:33.906 --> 01:16:35.708
- Huh.
- Cap. this is Joel.

1298
01:16:35.842 --> 01:16:37.410
Joel. Right.

1299
01:16:37.543 --> 01:16:39.983
Joel ended up traveling seven
days on the surface to get here.

1300
01:16:40.113 --> 01:16:42.182
- Seven days?
- Seven... Yeah. seven days.

1301
01:16:42.315 --> 01:16:44.784
- That is one hell of a journey. Joel.
- It was. Yeah.

1302
01:16:44.918 --> 01:16:46.953
I don't get it.
Why'd you leave your colony. Joel?

1303
01:16:47.087 --> 01:16:48.689
You get caught stealing food?

1304
01:16:48.823 --> 01:16:52.491
No. I didn't get caught stealing food.
Why is that such a thing?

1305
01:16:52.625 --> 01:16:54.360
He came for love.

1306
01:16:54.494 --> 01:16:56.028
Good on ya. mate.
That's beautiful.

1307
01:16:56.163 --> 01:16:58.933
There is no mission
more admirable than love.

1308
01:16:59.065 --> 01:17:01.367
Every sailor
worth his salt knows that.

1309
01:17:01.500 --> 01:17:03.436
Yo. Cap.
We cooking this shit or what?

1310
01:17:03.570 --> 01:17:05.872
Feel like I got King Kong's nuts
on my shoulders. man.

1311
01:17:06.006 --> 01:17:07.975
That's charming. Rock. really.

1312
01:17:08.107 --> 01:17:11.345
Joel. you look like a man who
knows his way around a barbecue.

1313
01:17:11.477 --> 01:17:14.147
- I... don't...
- Come help us get a fire started.

1314
01:17:14.280 --> 01:17:16.649
Um. actually. I'm gonna...

1315
01:17:16.783 --> 01:17:19.919
- catch up with Aimee for a sec. if it's...
- Yeah.

1316
01:17:20.052 --> 01:17:22.321
<b>CAP: I apologize.
I... Old habits.</b>

1317
01:17:22.455 --> 01:17:25.892
You show up and...
here I am trying to give you orders.

1318
01:17:26.025 --> 01:17:27.470
I'll give you guys
some privacy. yeah?

1319
01:17:27.494 --> 01:17:29.296
<i>- Thank you.
- Yeah. namaste.</i>

1320
01:17:29.430 --> 01:17:31.097
Uh. I was gonna just.
if you...

1321
01:17:31.230 --> 01:17:32.532
<b>- CAP: Hey. Joel.
- Yeah?</b>

1322
01:17:32.665 --> 01:17:34.601
We're throwing a killer
going-away party tonight.

1323
01:17:34.734 --> 01:17:35.968
Nothing fancy. but...

1324
01:17:36.102 --> 01:17:38.538
we'll have a drink together
to welcome you to the colony.

1325
01:17:38.672 --> 01:17:39.672
Okay.

1326
01:17:39.739 --> 01:17:40.939
First beer's on me.

1327
01:17:41.074 --> 01:17:42.476
Thanks.

1328
01:17:42.609 --> 01:17:44.144
He's nice.

1329
01:17:44.276 --> 01:17:45.578
Brews his own beer.

1330
01:17:45.713 --> 01:17:48.015
- Oh.
- Hello. darling. How are you?

1331
01:17:48.147 --> 01:17:50.150
Course he does.

1332
01:17:53.020 --> 01:17:55.589
I'm sorry. There's just so much
going on right now.

1333
01:17:55.722 --> 01:17:56.923
- Do you mind?
- Yeah.

1334
01:17:57.056 --> 01:17:58.090
It's crazy.

1335
01:17:58.225 --> 01:18:00.293
Pretty nice here. you know.

1336
01:18:00.427 --> 01:18:02.596
Why. uh...
why do you have to leave?

1337
01:18:02.730 --> 01:18:05.232
- It's beautiful. It's just not safe.
- Right.

1338
01:18:05.365 --> 01:18:06.932
Everyone's afraid.

1339
01:18:07.066 --> 01:18:10.503
Even your bunker got breached.
and you're all young and strong.

1340
01:18:10.637 --> 01:18:11.837
Yeah.

1341
01:18:11.972 --> 01:18:13.707
Hey. Aimee?

1342
01:18:13.841 --> 01:18:17.744
Sorry. I know you got. like.
a lot going on. but. uh...

1343
01:18:18.779 --> 01:18:21.948
you know. I came...
I came all the way here to see you.

1344
01:18:22.082 --> 01:18:25.619
and so I'm just...
checkin' in.

1345
01:18:25.753 --> 01:18:29.423
Just wondering how you're...
feeling about that.

1346
01:18:29.556 --> 01:18:31.991
I think it's the most romantic
thing anyone's ever done.

1347
01:18:32.124 --> 01:18:34.694
You do? Okay.
Okay. good. 'cause. um...

1348
01:18:34.828 --> 01:18:37.330
But listen. Joel. um...

1349
01:18:37.463 --> 01:18:40.499
talking to you on the radio
was such a nice escape

1350
01:18:40.633 --> 01:18:42.703
from the stress
of running this colony.

1351
01:18:42.837 --> 01:18:44.471
Yeah.

1352
01:18:44.604 --> 01:18:45.771
And. um...

1353
01:18:47.039 --> 01:18:50.442
I mean. you're probably the only
person left alive from my old life.

1354
01:18:50.909 --> 01:18:52.680
From Fairfield.

1355
01:18:55.914 --> 01:18:57.283
Oh. There's a...

1356
01:18:57.418 --> 01:19:00.855
There's a "but" coming.
isn't there?

1357
01:19:02.388 --> 01:19:05.793
But I didn't think
you'd actually come here. Joel.

1358
01:19:06.659 --> 01:19:08.028
Oh. Um...

1359
01:19:08.162 --> 01:19:10.231
And I am so happy to see you.

1360
01:19:10.364 --> 01:19:11.732
I'm just not...

1361
01:19:12.732 --> 01:19:15.269
I'm not the same person
that I used to be. you know?

1362
01:19:15.401 --> 01:19:17.637
Seven years. that's a long time.

1363
01:19:17.771 --> 01:19:21.208
I've... I've lost people.
My mom. my friends. and...

1364
01:19:21.875 --> 01:19:23.910
Last year I lost someone...

1365
01:19:25.378 --> 01:19:27.481
and he meant a lot to me.

1366
01:19:28.848 --> 01:19:30.150
Um...

1367
01:19:30.817 --> 01:19:32.153
Whew.

1368
01:19:51.472 --> 01:19:54.407
Oh. man. I feel
like such an idiot.

1369
01:19:54.540 --> 01:19:56.642
- No. No. don't.
- I didn't even...

1370
01:19:56.776 --> 01:19:59.712
I didn't even ask you
if I should come.

1371
01:19:59.846 --> 01:20:03.049
I just got so excited.
and I... I left.

1372
01:20:03.182 --> 01:20:05.285
I don't know what I thought.

1373
01:20:06.519 --> 01:20:08.521
Well. I know what I thought.

1374
01:20:08.655 --> 01:20:12.392
I'd come and...
and sweep you off your feet.

1375
01:20:12.525 --> 01:20:14.660
and we'd be happy.

1376
01:20:14.793 --> 01:20:16.095
Oh. Joel.

1377
01:20:16.230 --> 01:20:21.135
But you...
didn't w-want... me.

1378
01:20:21.267 --> 01:20:25.271
I am so sorry. I should have
said something on the radio or...

1379
01:20:25.405 --> 01:20:27.908
No. It's okay.
It's okay. Um...

1380
01:20:28.040 --> 01:20:31.278
I know this isn't how
you pictured this going. but...

1381
01:20:33.780 --> 01:20:35.515
you'll still
come with us. right?

1382
01:20:35.649 --> 01:20:39.587
Come with you...
Uh. on the... yacht?

1383
01:20:41.754 --> 01:20:43.990
This is our shot at survival.

1384
01:20:46.325 --> 01:20:47.895
Give Cap a chance.

1385
01:20:49.395 --> 01:20:51.364
<b>[LAUGHING. CHATTERING]</b>

1386
01:20:51.498 --> 01:20:53.667
<b>- [CAP MUTTERING]
- Tell us.</b>

1387
01:20:53.799 --> 01:20:56.003
<b>BILL: Yeah. come on. Cap.
Tell us another story.</b>

1388
01:20:56.136 --> 01:20:58.906
<b>- JANICE: Yeah. come on.
- Four years post-Agatha.</b>

1389
01:20:59.039 --> 01:21:00.974
HMS Brisbane. First watch.

1390
01:21:01.106 --> 01:21:03.310
I was the first person
to see it coming over the wall.

1391
01:21:03.442 --> 01:21:05.979
<b>- Giant lizard. two stories high.
- [ALL GASPING]</b>

1392
01:21:06.747 --> 01:21:10.484
I sounded the alarm.
Too late.

1393
01:21:10.616 --> 01:21:13.485
<b>- We lost 1.032 souls that night.
- [ALL GASPING]</b>

1394
01:21:13.619 --> 01:21:15.788
Those of us that survived
took to the sea.

1395
01:21:15.922 --> 01:21:20.127
I mean. make no mistake.
We have lost this war. Right?

1396
01:21:20.260 --> 01:21:23.997
There is no place for mankind on land.
But out there?

1397
01:21:24.129 --> 01:21:26.132
There we got a chance.

1398
01:21:26.266 --> 01:21:28.368
<b>[CLEARS THROAT]
I've got a...</b>

1399
01:21:28.502 --> 01:21:31.370
Sorry. Just got a... question.

1400
01:21:31.503 --> 01:21:33.506
I survived seven days
on the surface.

1401
01:21:33.640 --> 01:21:37.977
and... if I can do that.
literally anyone can.

1402
01:21:38.110 --> 01:21:41.280
Seven days on the surface?
I'm impressed.

1403
01:21:41.414 --> 01:21:44.583
So maybe we still have
a chance... to fight

1404
01:21:44.717 --> 01:21:47.754
and... and. you know. win. uh...

1405
01:21:47.887 --> 01:21:50.422
win our...
win our world back.

1406
01:21:50.556 --> 01:21:54.894
I have a plan. And if you have a
better one. mate. I'm... I'm all ears.

1407
01:21:55.028 --> 01:21:57.963
- And I will stand by your side.
- You wanna hear my...

1408
01:21:58.097 --> 01:22:00.232
You wanna hear my plan?

1409
01:22:00.366 --> 01:22:01.702
It's. uh...

1410
01:22:02.535 --> 01:22:04.070
just. uh...

1411
01:22:09.810 --> 01:22:12.212
<b>I got nothing. uh...
[CLEARS THROAT]</b>

1412
01:22:12.346 --> 01:22:13.812
Hey. that's on me.

1413
01:22:13.946 --> 01:22:16.848
I-I didn't mean to put you
on the spot. mate. It's...

1414
01:22:16.982 --> 01:22:20.653
<b>Well... [CHUCKLES] Aimee tells
me you make a mean minestrone.</b>

1415
01:22:21.421 --> 01:22:22.756
And you're great on the radio.

1416
01:22:22.888 --> 01:22:25.024
Lord knows
I need a comms expert.

1417
01:22:25.158 --> 01:22:28.595
<b>- Someone to teach Rocko how to cook.
- [ALL LAUGHING]</b>

1418
01:22:29.863 --> 01:22:33.700
Do you guys have a radio I could use?
I want to contact my colony.

1419
01:22:34.601 --> 01:22:38.105
7045. this is 3022.
Come in.

1420
01:22:40.440 --> 01:22:43.944
7045. this is 3022.
Is anyone there?

1421
01:22:44.078 --> 01:22:45.745
Tim? Ava?
Anyone. Over.

1422
01:22:45.878 --> 01:22:48.547
Cap thought you might
need a snack.

1423
01:22:48.681 --> 01:22:51.050
- Oh.
- You know. he brews his own beer.

1424
01:22:52.052 --> 01:22:54.488
- Yep. Yeah. I heard.
- It's good. man.

1425
01:22:54.620 --> 01:22:56.824
- Cool. Thank you.
- Yeah.

1426
01:23:39.966 --> 01:23:42.102
<b>[CHUCKLES]</b>

1427
01:23:46.272 --> 01:23:49.008
<b>[STATIC CRACKLING]</b>

1428
01:23:50.811 --> 01:23:52.846
<i><b>RAY: Hello? Is someone there?</b></i>

1429
01:23:52.979 --> 01:23:54.114
Hey. Yeah! Yeah!

1430
01:23:54.247 --> 01:23:56.348
Yeah. Ray. is that you?
It's me. It's Joel.

1431
01:23:56.481 --> 01:23:57.984
<i><b>Joel? [CHUCKLING]
Oh. my God!</b></i>

1432
01:23:58.118 --> 01:24:00.653
<i><b>- Hey. guys! It's Joel. He made it!
- [ALL CHATTERING ON RADIO]</b></i>

1433
01:24:00.787 --> 01:24:02.821
<i><b>- TIM: You're kidding!
- Hey. Hey. guys!</b></i>

1434
01:24:02.955 --> 01:24:05.391
It's me. It's Joel.
I'm... I'm... I'm safe.

1435
01:24:05.525 --> 01:24:07.627
I-I made it.
I'm at Aimee's colony.

1436
01:24:07.761 --> 01:24:09.638
<i><b>- TIM: He made it!
- KALA: Oh. my God. you're alive?</b></i>

1437
01:24:09.662 --> 01:24:11.040
It's so good
to hear your guys' voices.

1438
01:24:11.064 --> 01:24:12.633
<i><b>TIM: So good to hear you. too. buddy.</b></i>

1439
01:24:12.766 --> 01:24:14.577
<i><b>- KALA: Are you okay?
- I feel like it's been so long.</b></i>

1440
01:24:14.601 --> 01:24:17.246
<i><b>- I've got so much to tell you guys.
- KALA: Tell us what you've seen.</b></i>

1441
01:24:17.270 --> 01:24:21.040
<i><b>- I saw a queen Sandgobbler.
- TIM: What's a queen Sandgobbler?</b></i>

1442
01:24:21.173 --> 01:24:23.276
It's... I don't know.
but I blew it up.

1443
01:24:23.409 --> 01:24:24.912
I blew it up
with a hand grenade!

1444
01:24:25.044 --> 01:24:26.412
<i><b>RAY: Where'd you get a grenade?</b></i>

1445
01:24:26.546 --> 01:24:28.147
Yeah. it was so awesome. and...

1446
01:24:28.281 --> 01:24:31.918
What else? What else?
Uh. I met these two really cool survivors.

1447
01:24:32.052 --> 01:24:35.622
And they taught me all these things.
They live on the surface and...

1448
01:24:35.756 --> 01:24:37.990
And. oh. oh. oh!
I met a Mav1s.

1449
01:24:38.124 --> 01:24:41.627
<i><b>- I talked to a real live Mav1s.
- KALA: No way! What's she like?</b></i>

1450
01:24:41.761 --> 01:24:45.932
Uh. she was...
very informative. emotionally. and...

1451
01:24:46.065 --> 01:24:47.266
<b>[SIGHS]</b>

1452
01:24:47.400 --> 01:24:50.904
And I got a dog too. um...

1453
01:24:51.037 --> 01:24:54.475
<i><b>- RAY: Wow. Joel. You got a dog?
- KALA: And how is it with Aimee?</b></i>

1454
01:24:54.975 --> 01:24:56.610
Uh. really...

1455
01:24:57.209 --> 01:24:58.846
really good.

1456
01:24:58.979 --> 01:25:03.316
<i><b>KALA: Joel. you simply surviving
that journey. it's incredible.</b></i>

1457
01:25:03.449 --> 01:25:05.184
<i><b>RAY: We're proud of you. Joel.</b></i>

1458
01:25:06.619 --> 01:25:08.854
Man. I really miss you guys.

1459
01:25:10.123 --> 01:25:14.061
How is. uh... How is everything back there?
Give me the update.

1460
01:25:14.194 --> 01:25:17.030
<i><b>RAY: Not good.
We've had multiple breaches.</b></i>

1461
01:25:17.164 --> 01:25:19.332
Multiple breaches? What do you mean?
Is everyone okay?

1462
01:25:19.464 --> 01:25:22.467
<i>Not really. I don't think
we can stay here much longer.</i>

1463
01:25:22.601 --> 01:25:25.037
<b>[STATIC CRACKLING]</b>

1464
01:25:25.171 --> 01:25:26.539
Uh. guys?

1465
01:25:26.672 --> 01:25:28.283
<i><b>[RAY. BREAKING UP]
We're surviving for now.</b></i>

1466
01:25:28.307 --> 01:25:31.711
"Surviving for now."
What? Sur... Ray? Hey. guys!

1467
01:25:31.843 --> 01:25:34.515
<b>- [STATIC]
- Hey. no. no. no. no. no. no. no. Shit.</b>

1468
01:25:34.647 --> 01:25:38.051
<b>- Hello. guys. can you hear me?
- [STATIC CRACKLING]</b>

1469
01:25:38.185 --> 01:25:39.785
Guys?

1470
01:25:41.754 --> 01:25:43.656
<b>- [SWITCH CLICKS]
- [STATIC ENDS]</b>

1471
01:25:50.128 --> 01:25:51.832
I gotta go back.

1472
01:25:52.797 --> 01:25:54.700
What am I doing here?

1473
01:26:08.614 --> 01:26:10.584
Purple berries.

1474
01:26:19.525 --> 01:26:22.194
<i><b>CAP: Giant lizard. two stories high.
coming over the wall.</b></i>

1475
01:26:22.329 --> 01:26:25.465
<i><b>CLYDE: The lizard-looking ones
can't climb for shit.</b></i>

1476
01:26:25.597 --> 01:26:27.333
Lying son of a bitch.

1477
01:26:28.767 --> 01:26:30.604
Son of a bitch!

1478
01:26:36.342 --> 01:26:40.079
[FUNK MUSIC PLAYING ON SPEAKER]

1479
01:26:42.582 --> 01:26:45.185
Y'all like this shit. huh?

1480
01:26:45.319 --> 01:26:46.620
Aimee.

1481
01:26:46.753 --> 01:26:48.822
<b>- [BOTH LAUGHING]
- Hey. hey. Aimee. Aimee. Aimee.</b>

1482
01:26:48.954 --> 01:26:50.656
- Joel!
- Hey. hey. hey. hey. hey. Hey.

1483
01:26:50.789 --> 01:26:52.758
<b>- [WHISPERING] I have to talk to you.
- Joel!</b>

1484
01:26:53.860 --> 01:26:55.194
Oh. you're so drunk.

1485
01:26:55.328 --> 01:27:00.566
Hot. super ripped. super awesome
Joely-Joely Dawson!

1486
01:27:00.700 --> 01:27:02.269
<b>- [GIGGLES]
- Aimee. please.</b>

1487
01:27:02.401 --> 01:27:05.038
This is super important.
I need to talk to you about something.

1488
01:27:05.171 --> 01:27:08.007
You have to get everyone
out of here right now.

1489
01:27:08.141 --> 01:27:11.011
Okay. I think something bad is
about to happen. I'm telling you.

1490
01:27:11.144 --> 01:27:13.678
I can feel it. This is a bad...
This is a bad vibe.

1491
01:27:13.812 --> 01:27:16.649
<b>[FUNK MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]</b>

1492
01:27:16.781 --> 01:27:19.720
I think he's planning something.
I don't think he's here to save you.

1493
01:27:19.852 --> 01:27:22.122
- Who?
- The yacht captain. He tried to poison me.

1494
01:27:22.254 --> 01:27:25.691
Cap. Cap's right there.
He's dancing.

1495
01:27:26.793 --> 01:27:30.029
Oh. my... I hate him.
I hate him so much.

1496
01:27:30.163 --> 01:27:32.464
Listen. he gave me
these poison berries. okay?

1497
01:27:32.598 --> 01:27:35.038
And I know that the berries are
poison because my dog told me.

1498
01:27:35.067 --> 01:27:36.735
You have a talking dog?

1499
01:27:36.869 --> 01:27:38.970
- No. no. no. Aimee.
- I love dogs!

1500
01:27:39.105 --> 01:27:40.105
<b>[GROANS]</b>

1501
01:27:40.207 --> 01:27:43.644
What'd he say?
Where is the little fella?

1502
01:27:44.644 --> 01:27:45.764
<b>WOMAN: Man down!
[CHUCKLES]</b>

1503
01:27:45.845 --> 01:27:47.314
Please.
Please try to listen to me.

1504
01:27:47.446 --> 01:27:49.649
I need your help.
Something's gonna happen.

1505
01:27:49.783 --> 01:27:51.718
Your colony. they're in danger.

1506
01:27:51.851 --> 01:27:52.851
- Joel.
- What?

1507
01:27:52.918 --> 01:27:54.387
<b>- Joel!
- [GRUNTS]</b>

1508
01:27:56.289 --> 01:27:58.792
<b>[GROANS]</b>

1509
01:27:59.592 --> 01:28:02.829
<b>[MAN COUGHING. GROANING]</b>

1510
01:28:04.163 --> 01:28:06.165
Oh. shit.

1511
01:28:06.298 --> 01:28:08.567
- Aimee? Aimee?
- Joel? Joel. are you okay?

1512
01:28:08.700 --> 01:28:09.970
Good morning.

1513
01:28:10.102 --> 01:28:12.003
Joel. I'm sorry about
the fist to your face.

1514
01:28:12.137 --> 01:28:15.542
I couldn't have you talking shit about us
on the radio. I didn't wanna mess this up.

1515
01:28:15.674 --> 01:28:18.177
<b>- [GRUNTING]
- Dana. take care of it.</b>

1516
01:28:19.779 --> 01:28:22.582
Dana. d-don't.
Not the radio tower!

1517
01:28:22.714 --> 01:28:24.383
<b>[COLONISTS SHOUTING]</b>

1518
01:28:24.516 --> 01:28:27.887
<b>- MAN: What are you doing?
- WOMAN: Are you crazy?</b>

1519
01:28:28.021 --> 01:28:31.258
So. you probably figured out
we're not on a pleasure cruise.

1520
01:28:31.391 --> 01:28:34.528
My crew and I want to thank you
for your generous donations.

1521
01:28:34.660 --> 01:28:36.863
Food. water. supplies. medicine.

1522
01:28:36.995 --> 01:28:38.698
We greatly appreciate it.

1523
01:28:38.830 --> 01:28:42.334
It will see us through to the next
helpless colony down the coast.

1524
01:28:42.467 --> 01:28:43.802
<b>MAN: He's a food stealer!</b>

1525
01:28:43.936 --> 01:28:45.671
<b>- You're right.
- MAN: Yeah.</b>

1526
01:28:45.805 --> 01:28:49.042
But it's not that simple. The world
is basically devoid of fossil fuels.

1527
01:28:49.174 --> 01:28:51.077
Not enough to run
a yacht on. anyway.

1528
01:28:51.211 --> 01:28:54.446
So my crew and I.
we had to improvise just to survive.

1529
01:28:54.580 --> 01:28:58.016
And we found a real special fuel source.
Actually. Rocko did.

1530
01:28:58.150 --> 01:29:00.285
- Didn't ya. big fella?
- Yeah. that was me.

1531
01:29:00.419 --> 01:29:04.725
Ten tons of pure power.
chained to the front of that yacht.

1532
01:29:05.391 --> 01:29:06.993
She's sleeping now.

1533
01:29:08.494 --> 01:29:10.196
She will be hungry soon.

1534
01:29:17.838 --> 01:29:19.372
What?

1535
01:29:19.504 --> 01:29:21.240
Well. what can I say?

1536
01:29:23.008 --> 01:29:24.709
Shit gets crazy
in the apocalypse.

1537
01:29:24.843 --> 01:29:26.712
Oh. my God.

1538
01:29:26.846 --> 01:29:30.083
<b>[COLONISTS CHATTERING]</b>

1539
01:29:42.861 --> 01:29:45.397
<b>[RUMBLING]</b>

1540
01:29:48.333 --> 01:29:51.370
<b>- AIMEE: Oh. my God.
- [ALL SCREAMING]</b>

1541
01:29:52.271 --> 01:29:53.306
Run!

1542
01:29:54.440 --> 01:29:57.844
<b>[SCREAMING CONTINUES]</b>

1543
01:30:02.414 --> 01:30:03.283
Rose!

1544
01:30:03.415 --> 01:30:04.851
<b>[SCREAMING CONTINUES]</b>

1545
01:30:04.984 --> 01:30:06.086
<b>[AIMEE GRUNTING]</b>

1546
01:30:06.218 --> 01:30:09.221
<b>- [GROWLING]
- Oh. my God. we're gonna die.</b>

1547
01:30:09.355 --> 01:30:11.958
<b>[ROARING]</b>

1548
01:30:13.092 --> 01:30:15.928
Mkay. Just gotta find a way
to free my hands from the...

1549
01:30:16.061 --> 01:30:18.396
<b>- [BINDING SNAPS]
- Oh.</b>

1550
01:30:18.530 --> 01:30:21.533
I have to stop these bastards
from taking our stuff!

1551
01:30:21.668 --> 01:30:23.236
<b>Oh. my...
[SHOUTS]</b>

1552
01:30:24.336 --> 01:30:26.172
You traveled 85 miles
across hell.

1553
01:30:26.305 --> 01:30:28.074
I think
I can stop three assholes.

1554
01:30:28.208 --> 01:30:29.509
- You get the crab!
- What?

1555
01:30:31.644 --> 01:30:33.879
This is desperate.

1556
01:30:34.814 --> 01:30:38.017
<b>[SHOUTING. GRUNTING]</b>

1557
01:30:39.586 --> 01:30:42.088
<b>- Aimee?
- [ROARING CONTINUES]</b>

1558
01:31:01.274 --> 01:31:03.610
<b>[SHOUTING]</b>

1559
01:31:15.021 --> 01:31:17.323
<b>Holy shit.
[GASPS]</b>

1560
01:31:17.455 --> 01:31:18.458
Holy shit.

1561
01:31:18.591 --> 01:31:20.861
<b>[ROARING CONTINUES]</b>

1562
01:31:33.672 --> 01:31:36.342
<b>- [ELECTRICAL CHARGE ZAPS]
- [COLONISTS GASPING]</b>

1563
01:31:41.980 --> 01:31:44.350
<b>[BOTH GRUNTING]</b>

1564
01:31:49.588 --> 01:31:51.857
<b>- [SWITCH CLICKS]
- [ELECTRICAL CHARGE ZAPS]</b>

1565
01:31:51.990 --> 01:31:54.226
<b>[ROARING CONTINUES]</b>

1566
01:32:15.013 --> 01:32:17.182
<b>[SHOUTING]</b>

1567
01:32:17.949 --> 01:32:19.318
<b>[GROANS]</b>

1568
01:32:21.954 --> 01:32:24.257
<b>[COUGHS. GROANS]</b>

1569
01:32:25.391 --> 01:32:27.092
<b>- [ROARING CONTINUES]
- No. no. no. no. no!</b>

1570
01:32:27.226 --> 01:32:30.263
<b>[GRUNTING CONTINUES]</b>

1571
01:32:32.998 --> 01:32:34.601
<b>[BARKING]</b>

1572
01:32:35.567 --> 01:32:37.570
Boy? Boy!

1573
01:32:39.172 --> 01:32:41.374
<b>- Boy! Hey!
- [BARKING CONTINUES]</b>

1574
01:32:45.677 --> 01:32:47.646
Dana? Shoot the dog.

1575
01:32:48.547 --> 01:32:50.215
<b>[GRUNTS]</b>

1576
01:33:03.195 --> 01:33:04.564
<b>[AIMEE GROANING]</b>

1577
01:33:04.696 --> 01:33:05.998
<b>JOEL: Aimee!</b>

1578
01:33:07.699 --> 01:33:09.336
<b>JOEL: No!</b>

1579
01:33:11.169 --> 01:33:13.839
Rocko? Time to go. Let's mo...

1580
01:33:13.972 --> 01:33:16.342
