- [GROWLING]</b>

1618
01:35:19.031 --> 01:35:21.601
<b>[GROANS. COUGHING]</b>

1619
01:35:48.127 --> 01:35:50.129
Oh. my God.

1620
01:35:57.503 --> 01:36:00.540
Oh. shit. we're gonna die.
We're dying.

1621
01:36:01.973 --> 01:36:03.409
<b>[WHINES]</b>

1622
01:36:07.812 --> 01:36:10.048
<b>No!
[SCREAMING]</b>

1623
01:36:10.182 --> 01:36:12.452
<b>[SCREAMING]</b>

1624
01:36:17.890 --> 01:36:20.560
<b>[GRUNTING. SCREAMS]</b>

1625
01:36:22.328 --> 01:36:25.198
<b>[ALL GASPING. GROANING]</b>

1626
01:36:31.104 --> 01:36:32.504
That was amazing.

1627
01:36:32.637 --> 01:36:33.838
What? Uh...

1628
01:36:34.405 --> 01:36:36.042
- Amazing? Me?
- Yeah.

1629
01:36:36.174 --> 01:36:37.577
You thought I was...

1630
01:36:45.150 --> 01:36:46.919
- Thank you. Joel.
- Yeah?

1631
01:36:47.052 --> 01:36:50.890
Yeah. well. I would've done it
different. but... you did all right.

1632
01:36:51.022 --> 01:36:52.859
Oh. Okay.

1633
01:36:52.991 --> 01:36:55.494
Sorry. Yeah. just...

1634
01:36:55.628 --> 01:36:57.362
That's looking better.
Take care of it.

1635
01:36:57.495 --> 01:36:58.964
<b>- ROSE: Bye now.
- Bye. guys.</b>

1636
01:37:00.266 --> 01:37:02.735
- Can you move this? Yeah.
- Aimee.

1637
01:37:06.472 --> 01:37:08.307
- Hey.
- Hey. Um...

1638
01:37:08.440 --> 01:37:11.810
I gotta get back to my colony.
see if they're okay.

1639
01:37:11.944 --> 01:37:13.846
Right. yeah. Yeah.

1640
01:37:13.979 --> 01:37:17.150
Some friends of mine told me that
there's a place in the mountains.

1641
01:37:17.283 --> 01:37:19.151
I guess.
that's safe from the monsters.

1642
01:37:19.284 --> 01:37:21.753
So maybe we'll all head there.

1643
01:37:21.887 --> 01:37:23.056
Oh.

1644
01:37:23.189 --> 01:37:27.125
Um. it was really cool to just...
to see you in action.

1645
01:37:27.260 --> 01:37:32.497
and... I don't know. how you take
care of all these people. and then...

1646
01:37:32.631 --> 01:37:35.834
- Oh.
- I'm so glad you came.

1647
01:37:40.006 --> 01:37:41.039
I gotta go.

1648
01:37:41.172 --> 01:37:42.907
I'm worried about 'em.

1649
01:37:43.042 --> 01:37:44.444
Yeah.

1650
01:37:45.511 --> 01:37:48.348
But I had something
for you. Um...

1651
01:37:48.948 --> 01:37:50.850
Oh. my God.

1652
01:37:50.982 --> 01:37:52.150
Crocodile Carl?

1653
01:37:52.284 --> 01:37:54.352
<b>- Oh. my God.
- I know. [CHUCKLES]</b>

1654
01:37:54.486 --> 01:37:57.589
Thought you should
have him back finally.

1655
01:37:58.757 --> 01:37:59.791
Here. uh...

1656
01:38:01.125 --> 01:38:03.529
- No. I can't take that. You need it.
- No. no. no.

1657
01:38:03.662 --> 01:38:06.432
I want you to take it.
It'd mean a lot to me.

1658
01:38:06.565 --> 01:38:08.534
Really. take it.

1659
01:38:10.002 --> 01:38:13.239
I got it all up here. anyway.
So I can always make copies.

1660
01:38:13.372 --> 01:38:15.941
Thanks for inspiring me to...

1661
01:38:17.241 --> 01:38:19.278
take this trip.

1662
01:38:19.410 --> 01:38:21.381
It's the best decision
I ever made.

1663
01:38:22.547 --> 01:38:25.950
All right.
uh. I'm gonna go.

1664
01:38:26.084 --> 01:38:28.119
- Yeah.
- Boy. come on!

1665
01:38:28.253 --> 01:38:30.222
Um...

1666
01:38:30.355 --> 01:38:32.824
- Uh. be careful.
- Yeah. you. too.

1667
01:38:34.493 --> 01:38:36.296
- Bye. Aimee.
- Bye.

1668
01:38:59.317 --> 01:39:00.820
That was...

1669
01:39:00.953 --> 01:39:02.888
- Great.
- Yeah.

1670
01:39:03.021 --> 01:39:04.489
<b>[LAUGHS]</b>

1671
01:39:10.195 --> 01:39:11.931
I'll come find you.

1672
01:39:14.266 --> 01:39:15.734
You better.

1673
01:39:20.239 --> 01:39:21.473
Okay.

1674
01:39:30.882 --> 01:39:32.918
<i><b>JOEL: My name is Joel Dawson.</b></i>

1675
01:39:33.052 --> 01:39:37.557
<i>I'm 24 years old.
and I survived seven days on the surface.</i>

1676
01:39:38.556 --> 01:39:42.360
<b>[CREATURE ROARING. SHRIEKING]</b>

1677
01:39:42.494 --> 01:39:43.796
<b>[MUTTERING]</b>

1678
01:39:45.530 --> 01:39:47.100
<i>Twice. actually.</i>

1679
01:39:58.944 --> 01:40:00.178
- Joel?
- Joel?

1680
01:40:00.312 --> 01:40:02.547
<b>- [CHATTERING. GASPING]
- You guys! Hey!</b>

1681
01:40:02.681 --> 01:40:04.950
- Oh. my God!
- Hey. hey. hey!

1682
01:40:05.083 --> 01:40:07.120
<b>[CHATTERING. LAUGHING]</b>

1683
01:40:18.129 --> 01:40:21.366
I'm alive because of the
generosity of a few strangers

1684
01:40:21.499 --> 01:40:24.770
and the kindness of a great dog.

1685
01:40:26.538 --> 01:40:28.973
<i>My colony and I
are headed to the mountains.</i>

1686
01:40:29.106 --> 01:40:31.877
<i>There's supposed to be
less monsters there.</i>

1687
01:40:32.011 --> 01:40:36.381
<i>And don't get me wrong.
The surface is a dangerous place.</i>

1688
01:40:36.515 --> 01:40:40.319
<i>But I don't think hiding
underground is the answer anymore.</i>

1689
01:40:40.453 --> 01:40:45.658
<i>There is a great big. beautiful.
inspiring world out there.</i>

1690
01:40:45.790 --> 01:40:49.494
<i><b>[ON RADIO] And I know you think it
might be impossible. but it's not.</b></i>

1691
01:40:49.628 --> 01:40:51.796
<i>If I can survive out here.
anybody can.</i>

1692
01:40:51.931 --> 01:40:54.165
<i>It's like a good friend
once told me.</i>

1693
01:40:54.298 --> 01:40:57.069
<i>Good instincts are earned
by making mistakes.</i>

1694
01:40:57.202 --> 01:40:59.671
<i>If you're lucky enough
to survive a few mistakes.</i>

1695
01:40:59.805 --> 01:41:01.472
<i>you're gonna
do all right out here.</i>

1696
01:41:01.605 --> 01:41:05.510
<i>In this recording. you'll find
everything I know about our new world.</i>

1697
01:41:05.645 --> 01:41:07.513
<i>Most of this
I had to learn the hard way.</i>

1698
01:41:07.646 --> 01:41:09.948
<i>Hopefully. it'll make your way
a little easier.</i>

1699
01:41:10.583 --> 01:41:13.352
<i>So crank open that hatch.</i>

1700
01:41:13.485 --> 01:41:14.820
Okay. come on.

1701
01:41:14.954 --> 01:41:18.857
<i>Breathe some fresh air.
Go. Live your life.</i>

1702
01:41:19.924 --> 01:41:23.061
<i>It won't be easy.
but it'll be worth it.</i>

1703
01:41:24.564 --> 01:41:28.868
<i>I traveled 85 miles to find what I had
been missing below ground for seven years</i>

1704
01:41:29.000 --> 01:41:31.470
<i>was right above my head
this whole time.</i>

1705
01:41:31.604 --> 01:41:33.305
<i>And it's incredible.</i>

1706
01:41:34.339 --> 01:41:37.342
<i>Oh. and one last thing.
Don't settle.</i>

1707
01:41:37.476 --> 01:41:41.647
<i>You don't have to.
Not even at the end of the world.</i>

1708
01:41:49.521 --> 01:41:51.223
<i>Signing off.</i>

1709
01:41:51.355 --> 01:41:53.124
<i>Joel Dawson.</i>

1710
01:42:21.686 --> 01:42:24.155
<b>MINNOW: "Don't settle"?
That's my line.</b>

1711
01:42:24.289 --> 01:42:27.058
It's a long journey. kid.
I hope you know what you're doing.

1712
01:42:27.191 --> 01:42:29.994
<b>MINNOW: He definitely doesn't.
Snow Spiders will probably get him.</b>

1713
01:42:30.128 --> 01:42:31.629
<b>CLYDE: That's not a good way to go.</b>

1714
01:42:31.762 --> 01:42:33.131
<b>MINNOW: They will tear him apart.</b>

1715
01:42:33.265 --> 01:42:36.302
<b>- CLYDE: Nah. he'll figure it out.
- MINNOW: Possibly.</b>

1716
01:43:47.672 --> 01:43:49.241
<b>[WINGS FLUTTER]</b>

